gs it home no matter what.\n\nThe "Follow Me" feature captures cinematic footage without touching controls. I''ve shot my grandkids'' football games with broadcast quality. My wife''s book club. Family reunions that look like professional documentaries.\n\nMy veteran buddies didn''t believe me until they tried it themselves. Now there''s a group of twelve retired military pilots who fly GhostWings together every month. Most of us are in our 60s and 70s. We''ve all agreed‚Äîthis is the most impressive flight technology we''ve used since leaving active duty.\n\nGhostWing is completely waterproof, handles freezing cold and scorching heat, and it''s virtually indestructible. Same military-grade materials I trusted my life with.\n\nWhen GhostWing launched, it spread like wildfire in the military community. It sold out within 48 hours and developed a waitlist of over 10,000 orders. Professional photographers and filmmakers have made the switch.\n\nAdam has tripled production and is offering a 50%% discount for anyone who orders within the next 24 hours. You can get even deeper discounts by ordering multiple GhostWings, making it a perfect gift.\n\nMy advice: grab one for yourself and a few more for your friends and family. If a combat pilot says this is easy, trust me‚Äîanyone can fly it. Click on the link below this video to visit the official website and order with 50%% off.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1043, '2026-01-18T08:59:04.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recQoW9XHt2mIbv2m', 'GhostWing - Script 1057 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', 'Big drone companies have been keeping a secret from you. They''ve been making drones complicated on purpose so you keep buying the newest, most expensive model every year. But a former US military engineer just exposed their entire racket with a $99 drone so simple to fly that a 70-year-old man with no tech experience mastered it in under 60 seconds. Here''s how it happened. This drone was originally created for the US Special Forces by Captain Adam Scott, a 44-year-old US Army officer and leading engineer. He and his team were assigned to develop cutting-edge optical equipment for a critical mission in the Middle East. The mission required the Special Forces to capture enemy positions from miles away without ever being detected. After months of research and development, they created a groundbreaking prototype and the results were incredible. Celebrated as the most successful military invention in recent years, it was the first to ever use the patented MOT military optical technology. Meaning it''s at least 20 times more powerful than any commercially available drone, which gives it incredible capabilities. It can literally capture anything from tens of miles away with stunning 4K quality. Now here''s where the story gets interesting. When Adam showed the prototype to Pentagon officials, one of the generals, a 67-year-old man who openly admitted he could barely work his iPhone, asked to try it. Adam hesitated, worried the general would crash a multi-million dollar prototype. But within seconds, the general had it hovering perfectly, capturing crystal-clear reconnaissance footage like he''d been flying drones his entire career. That moment changed everything for Adam. He realized the military''s requirement for "any soldier can operate it under stress" had accidentally created the most user-friendly drone in history. He knew this technology had to reach the general public. As the original creator, he quickly secured all the permissions needed to redevelop it for mass production. He called it Ghostwing and it''s the most powerful drone ever made, built with one obsession: absolute simplicity. It uses a combination of military grade nanotechnology and unique materials to achieve the level of quality and utility of the top drone models but for a fraction of the price. Adam developed his own software that increases the drone''s power and control by 120%, but more importantly, it eliminates every frustrating thing about flying a drone. There are no complicated apps to download. No 40-page instruction manuals. No calibration nightmares. You take it out of the box, press one button, and it''s in the air. That''s it. The controller has large, clearly labeled buttons designed for comfort, not tiny controls that strain your eyes and cramp your fingers. It''s loaded with cutting edge technology like the "follow me" feature, which lets you take amazing videos of yourself without even touching the controller. Just go about your day and the Ghostwing captures it all beautifully. The advanced GPS functionality means it can track your location within 900 meters and return to you quickly when experiencing a weak signal or when the battery is low. And the collision detection function prevents any accidental crash or damage, making this drone the safest quadcopter ever engineered. It is literally impossible to crash this drone. The military made sure of that. And because it''s made of the best military materials available, it''s virtually indestructible. It''s completely waterproof and strong enough to withstand both freezing and scorcing hot temperatures. And what''s best about this drone is that you can use it for thousands of different purposes. Check your gutters without risking a fall on a ladder. Keep an eye on your property while you''re away. Record your grandkids'' recitals and ball games from angles that would make a Hollywood director jealous. Capture stunning aerial footage of your vacations and road trips. The possibilities with the Ghostwing are endless. When Adam first launched Ghostwing, it spread like wildfire in the military community. What he didn''t expect was for thousands of retired Americans to start flooding social media with jaw-dropping footage, proving you don''t need to be young or tech-savvy to create professional quality videos. After going viral, it sold out within the first 48 hours and quickly developed a waitlist of over 10,000 orders from all around the world. Celebrities, professional photographers and filmmakers, all made the switch to it. Adam wants everyone to know about this new technology, so he has since tripled the production and is offering a 50% discount for anyone who orders it within the next 24 hours. You can get even more discounts by ordering multiple Ghostwings, making it a perfect gift for anyone, especially someone who''s been told they''re "too old" for new technology. My advice, grab one for yourself and more for your friends and family before this amazing deal is taken down. Click on the link below this video to visit the official website and order with 50% off.', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1057, '2026-02-10T06:07:13.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recRFgb0b6qjm6erb', 'VitalTac - Script 1072 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('I almost died on a camping trip last October. Not from a bear. Not from a fall. From something so stupid it''s embarrassing.\n\nI got separated from my group two hours before dark. No cell service. No GPS signal. My cheap flashlight died after 45 minutes. And the temperature was dropping fast.\n\nI spent six hours stumbling through complete darkness, tripping over roots, walking in circles, getting more hypothermic by the minute. Search and rescue found me at 4 AM. Another two hours and I would have been a statistic.\n\nWhen I got home, I swore I''d never be that unprepared again. I started researching serious survival gear. That''s when I found out what Special Forces actually carry.\n\nNot the garbage they sell at REI. Not the "tactical" marketing nonsense at sporting goods stores. The actual equipment that American operators bring into hostile territory when failure means death.\n\nThe flashlight they use can do things I didn''t think were physically possible.\n\nStart fires with no matches, no lighter, no friction. Just point the beam at kindling. The concentrated light intensity creates ignition in under 10 seconds. You could be soaking wet, hands shaking from cold, and you can still make fire.\n\nSignal rescue aircraft from 2 miles away. The beam is so powerful that search teams can spot it from helicopters. That''s not an exaggeration ‚Äî that''s what it was designed for. Operators in enemy territory needed a way to mark their position for extraction without giving away their location with sound.\n\nLight up an entire mountainside like daylight. The Cree LED technology outputs 20 times more power than commercial flashlights. You can illuminate your entire campsite and the surrounding hundred yards with one handheld device.\n\nAnd this thing does not die.\n\nAircraft-grade titanium body. The same material on fifth-generation stealth fighters. Submerge it in a river ‚Äî keeps working. Drop it off a cliff ‚Äî keeps working. Freeze it overnight ‚Äî keeps working. Run over it with your truck ‚Äî keeps working.\n\nThe flashlight is called VitalTac. It was restricted to military use for years. Then a retired Special Forces operator rebuilt it for civilians. Same technology. Same materials. Same fire-starting, rescue-signaling, darkness-destroying capabilities. Just modified enough to be legal for civilian ownership.\n\nI''ve tested it for three months now. I''ve started campfires in the rain with nothing but the beam. I''ve lit up targets so far away my friends thought I was lying about the distance. I''ve dropped it, frozen it, submerged it. The thing is indestructible.\n\nBut here''s what you need to know. The Product Safety Commission is actively working to reclassify VitalTac as military equipment. When that happens, you won''t be able to buy it online. It''s already banned from Amazon and eBay. The only place left is the official website.\n\nIf you spend any time outdoors ‚Äî hiking, camping, hunting, fishing, or just driving through remote areas ‚Äî you need this. Not want. Need. The difference between a $30 flashlight and VitalTac is the difference between being a statistic and walking out alive.\n\nI keep one in my pack now. One in my truck. One at home. Because I remember those six hours in the dark. I remember the cold setting in. I remember thinking about my family and wondering if they''d ever know what happened to me.\n\nThat''s never happening again.\n\nRight now, VitalTac is 50%% off through the official site. The operator who builds these wants families to have the same protection that kept him alive overseas. He''s not getting rich off this ‚Äî he''s making sure regular people can access military-grade gear before the government takes that option away.\n\nClick the link below. Get yours before the regulation passes. Because the wilderness doesn''t care how prepared you think you are. It only cares how prepared you actually are.\n\nTap the link now.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1072, '2026-02-20T11:44:40.000Z');
