echnology from Apache helicopters. Your footage stays smooth even if your hands are shaking. The optical system uses MOT military optical technology, the same foundation Captain Scott built for combat reconnaissance. It captures four-K video that looks like it cost ten thousand dollars to produce.\n\nThe collision detection steers around obstacles automatically. The GPS brings it home if the signal drops. My father-in-law has never lost it or crashed it despite flying it dozens of times.\n\nSince Christmas he has documented every family event. His grandson''s Little League championship. His wife''s garden in full bloom. The surprise party we threw for his fiftieth anniversary. Every video looks professional. Every memory is preserved in a way we never imagined possible.\n\nOther family members started asking where he got it. Then they started buying their own.\n\nThis year we are giving GhostWings to everyone. My mother. My brother. My nephew who just bought his first house. At ninety-nine dollars with the current discount it costs less than most gifts that get forgotten by February.\n\nWhen GhostWing first launched it sold out in forty-eight hours. The waiting list hit ten thousand names. Families like ours discovered that professional quality footage no longer requires professional prices.\n\nCaptain Scott has finally caught up with demand and is offering fifty percent off for the next twenty-four hours. The discounts get deeper when you order multiple units, which is perfect for checking off your entire gift list at once.\n\nStop giving gifts that end up in drawers. Click the link below this video to visit the official GhostWing website and give someone the ability to capture memories that last forever.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1035, '2026-01-18T08:44:22.000Z');
