ust smooth, steady flight.\nOne customer said:\n‚ÄúI‚Äôm 71 and flew it perfectly my first time.‚Äù\nAnother said:\n‚ÄúI was nervous, but this thing does everything for you.‚Äù\nAnd this one says it all:\n‚ÄúI thought drones weren‚Äôt for people my age. I was wrong.‚Äù\nThis drone is called GhostWing.\nAnd it was designed for people who want incredible results ‚Äî without learning anything new.\nIt shoots stunning 4K video.\nIt has Follow Me mode, so it records you without touching the controller.\nIts advanced GPS tracks you up to 900 meters and safely brings itself home if the battery runs low.\nWorried about crashing?\nDon‚Äôt be.\nIt has built-in collision detection that avoids obstacles automatically.\nTrees.\n Roofs.\n Walls.\nIt steers away before anything happens.\nThe body is made from military-grade composite materials.\nThat means it‚Äôs waterproof, shock-resistant, and tough enough for real-world use.\nCold weather.\n Hot weather.\n Rain.\nNo problem.\nAnd the best part?\nYou don‚Äôt need it for ‚Äútech stuff.‚Äù\nUse it to capture family moments.\n Check your property from above.\n Record trips and memories.\nOr just enjoy flying something amazing ‚Äî without stress.\nWhen GhostWing was first released, it sold out in 48 hours.\nNot because of ads.\nBecause people shared the videos they took with it.\nA waitlist quickly grew to over 10,000 people worldwide.\nNow Adam has increased production.\nAnd for a limited time, he‚Äôs offering 50%% off.\nThat brings the price down to just $99.\nBut once this batch is gone, availability is not guaranteed.\nIf you‚Äôve ever thought,\n ‚ÄúI‚Äôm not good with technology anymore‚Äù ‚Äî\nThis was made for you.\nClick the link below now.\n Get your GhostWing today.\n And see how easy flying a drone really is ‚Äî even now.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1018, '2026-01-05T15:51:09.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recS8RLXoRS5zQseL', 'GhostWing - Script 1021 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('Every drone company has been lying to you about what "beginner-friendly" actually means.\nTom spent 30 years as a firefighter saving lives. When he retired, all he wanted was to capture his grandkids'' soccer games from the air‚Äîthose sweeping shots that turn ordinary moments into memories worth keeping forever.\nSo he did what most folks do. He bought a drone. Name brand. Supposed to be "easy to fly."\nWhat a joke.\nFirst flight sounded like a chainsaw mating with a blender. His grandson covered his ears and ran inside crying.\nSecond flight, the wind kicked up maybe ten miles per hour. The drone started shaking like a drunk hummingbird. Footage looked like it was filmed during an earthquake.\nThird flight? Clipped a tree branch. Crashed. Shattered into a dozen pieces on his driveway.\nThree hundred dollars gone. Just like that.\nBut here''s what really burned Tom up‚Ä¶\nIt wasn''t the money. It was the instruction manual. Forty-seven pages of tiny print. An app that needed a computer science degree to figure out. Buttons so small his arthritic fingers couldn''t even press them properly.\nHe felt like the drone was designed to make him feel stupid.\nTom was frustrated, but he wasn''t done. He started digging. Researching. Talking to buddies who flew drones in the military.\nThat''s when he discovered something that changed everything.\nTurns out, the big drone companies have been holding back. The technology for rock-solid, whisper-quiet, genuinely simple flight has existed for years. Military uses it. Hollywood uses it.\nBut they keep it locked up in drones that cost three, four, five thousand dollars‚Äîand still require a pilot''s learning curve.\nUntil now.\nA small team of engineers‚Äîtwo of them grandparents themselves‚Äîfigured out how to pack tactical-grade stabilization into something the size of a water bottle.\nBut here''s what made their mission different:\nThey didn''t just want to build a better drone. They wanted to build a drone that anyone over fifty could fly on their very first try. No manual. No app headaches. No tiny buttons. No frustration.\nThey call it the Ghost Wing.\nHere''s what makes the Ghost Wing completely different from every overpriced piece of junk collecting dust in your closet:\nIt''s silent. Not "kind of quiet"‚Äîsilent. The motor technology came straight from covert military operations where noise meant danger. You can fly this thing at a family barbecue, at your granddaughter''s graduation, at a peaceful morning at the lake‚Äîwithout everyone plugging their ears or giving you dirty looks.\nIt doesn''t shake. The gyroscopic stabilization holds steady in winds that would send other drones spinning into the neighbor''s pool. Your footage comes out smooth as butter. Every. Single. Time. No more earthquake videos.\nIt survives mistakes. Drop it. Crash it. Smack it into your garage door. The reinforced frame laughs it off. One customer dropped his from thirty feet onto concrete. Turned it back on. Flew away like nothing happened.\nAnd here''s the big one‚Äîanyone can fly it.\nWe''re not talking "easy with practice." We''re talking your-first-time easy.\nTom''s wife is seventy-two years old. Never touched a drone in her life. Thought they were "young people gadgets."\nShe had the Ghost Wing in the air within three minutes.\nHere''s why:\nOne button to take off. Press it. The drone rises smoothly to the perfect height and hovers there, steady as a rock, waiting for you.\nOne button to land. Press it. Sets down soft as a feather, right where you''re standing.\nOne button to come home. Flying over the trees and lose sight of it? Don''t panic. Press the button. It flies itself right back to you. Every time.\nNo joystick juggling. No phone apps crashing. No squinting at tiny screens.\nThe controller fits naturally in your hands with buttons large enough to actually feel and press. The screen shows exactly what the drone sees‚Äîbright, clear, simple.\nYour grandkids won''t need to help you figure it out. You''ll be teaching them.\nThe camera captures everything in crystal-clear 4K‚Äîthe same quality you see in nature documentaries.\nExcept now, you''re the one behind the lens.\nBirthday parties. Family reunions. That fishing trip with your son. Your property from angles you''ve never seen. The grandkids running through the sprinklers.\nThese aren''t just videos. They''re heirlooms.\nNow, here''s where the big drone companies got really angry.\nThe Ghost Wing team decided not to play their pricing games. No thousand-dollar markups. No "professional-only" gatekeeping.\nThey''re selling direct. Cutting out the middlemen. Cutting out the retail markups.\nAnd right now, they''ve got a launch special running:\nFifty percent off.\nHalf price for something that outperforms drones costing five times as much‚Äîand is ten times easier to fly.\nBut they can''t keep this price forever.\nTheir last three shipments sold out completely. The factories can only produce so many of the specialized silent motors.\nOnce this batch is gone, the discount goes with it.\nAnd here''s the part that makes this a complete no-brainer:\nYou''re protected for a full ninety days.\nThree entire months to put the Ghost Wing through its paces.\nIf it doesn''t blow your mind‚Ä¶ if it doesn''t capture footage that makes your friends ask "How''d you do that?"‚Ä¶ if you don''t find yourself reaching for it every single weekend‚Ä¶\nSend it back. Full refund. No questions. No hassles. No guilt trips.\nNinety days. That''s how confident they are you''ll love it.\nTom''s got one now. Uses it every weekend.\nHis grandkids fight over who gets to watch the footage with him. They call him "Papa Hollywood."\nThat fancy name-brand drone that shattered on his driveway? He uses the box for storage in the garage.\nHis wife? She''s already planning to film her garden from above this spring.\nClick below to see if the Ghost Wing is still in stock at the discounted price.\nThis military-grade silent drone is flying off shelves‚Äîand once this batch is gone, so is the fifty percent off.\nDon''t let complicated technology steal another moment worth capturing.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1021, '2026-01-11T12:55:15.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recSpbpez3NUCuyA3', 'VitalTac - Script 1004 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('This military flashlight is basically a real life lightsaber that fits in your pocket.\nBut I gotta warn you right now. This is not some cheap twenty dollar gas station flashlight. At six hundred dollars... this was never meant for civilians. It''s so powerful it melts through solid materials and can start a fire on command.\nThat''s exactly why the military kept it classified. Until now.\nThis thing throws a beam you can see from over two miles away. It was built specifically for American Special Forces. Designed to expose enemy positions in total darkness. And dominate close quarters combat when lives are on the line.\nThe secret is military grade Cree LED technology that makes this at least twenty times more powerful than anything you''ve ever held in your hand. That''s not an exaggeration. That''s why it literally burns through wood... plastic... even metal... in seconds.\nFor years this technology was completely locked away. Civilians couldn''t touch it.\nThen something changed.\nA decorated Special Forces operator retired from service. This man had carried this exact flashlight on missions in places you''ll never hear about. And he couldn''t forget what it meant to him. How many times it kept him alive.\nSo he memorized every detail of the design. And he built one in his garage.\nWithin days... military lawyers showed up at his door. They told him he couldn''t copy the design or he''d face serious consequences.\nMost guys would''ve walked away right there.\nNot him.\nHe saw it as an opportunity. A chance to fix everything that frustrated him during real combat missions. To make it even better. To adapt it for survival... for home defense... for people like you and me.\nAfter months of work he came out with something even more powerful than the original. Same classified technology. Same devastating power. But now completely legal for American civilians to own.\nHe''s the only person in the country licensed to manufacture it.\nHe calls it VitalTac.\nVitalTac is the most powerful flashlight ever sold to the public. And that''s not marketing talk.\nLook at this. See that? It overpowers a car''s headlights without even trying.\nThe body is forged from the same aluminum titanium alloy they use on fifth generation stealth fighter jets. Engineered to survive crushing pressure... extreme heat... and brutal combat conditions.\nWhich means VitalTac is basically indestructible.\nThrow it underwater. Works perfectly.\nFreeze it solid. Fires right up.\nDrop it in boiling water. Not a scratch.\nToss it in open flames. Keeps beaming.\nRun it over with a truck. Still works.\nThere''s nothing you can do to kill this flashlight.\nBut here''s where it gets interesting.\nVitalTac isn''t just tough. It''s a complete survival system.\nThat beam is hot enough to cook food if you need to. Powerful enough to signal rescue helicopters from miles away with the built in SOS mode. And that strobe function? One flash in an attacker''s eyes and they''re blind long enough for you to escape or protect your family.\nThis is the flashlight you hope you never need. But you''ll thank God you had it when everything goes wrong.\nNow if you want one... you need to hear this.\nWhile it''s completely legal right now... the US Product Safety Commission is working to reclassify this as military grade defense equipment. When that happens... it''s gone. You won''t find it anywhere online.\nThat''s already why Amazon won''t touch it. eBay banned it too.\nThe only place you can get a VitalTac is the official website. And right now... today only... you can grab one at fifty percent off.\nClick the link on your screen. See VitalTac in action yourself. And decide if you deserve this kind of protection.\nBefore the government makes that decision for you.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1004, '2025-12-25T18:03:27.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recSxIw2AuMFroc4z', 'GhostWing - Script 1024 - Waqar', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recpEWhnPcHgw5NmN', printf('You''ll never feel stupid trying to fly a drone again after seeing this.\nDJI and the big drone companies pray you never find out about this.\nThis tiny military-grade drone is so simple that a 72-year-old grandmother flew it on her first try ‚Äî in under three minutes. Just press one button to take off, one button to land, one button to bring it home. No manual. No apps. No confusion.\nIt''s called the Ghost Wing ‚Äî a pocket-sized drone that, once unboxed, gives you instant access to stunning 4K aerial footage without any of the headaches, crashes, or complicated controls that plague every other drone on the market.\nImagine capturing your grandkids'' soccer games, family reunions, and your property from angles you''ve never seen ‚Äî footage so smooth it looks like a Hollywood movie ‚Äî without reading a single page of instructions. It''s so easy, it almost feels like cheating. But I assure you, it''s not.\nLet me break it down for you.\nInstead of wasting three hundred dollars on a "beginner-friendly" drone that screams like a chainsaw, shakes in the slightest breeze, and shatters the first time it clips a tree branch, Ghost Wing gives you military-grade stability, whisper-silent flight, and a crash-proof frame ‚Äî all controlled with three simple buttons.\nIt all started in 2019.\nMarcus Chen, a retired military drone engineer who spent 22 years developing classified surveillance technology for the Department of Defense ‚Äî the same kind of tech used by elite special forces units ‚Äî left government work to visit his grandchildren in Ohio. While there, he watched his 68-year-old brother-in-law waste an entire afternoon trying to fly a brand-name drone. The thing crashed twice, the app froze three times, and the footage looked like it was filmed during an earthquake.\nHis brother-in-law ‚Äî a man who ran a successful construction company for 40 years ‚Äî sat there looking defeated. "I guess I''m just too old for this stuff," he said.\nThat moment changed everything.\nMarcus called his former colleague David Holloway, another retired military engineer. Together, they assembled a small team ‚Äî three retired military drone specialists, two of them grandparents themselves ‚Äî and set out to build something the industry said was impossible: a drone with military-grade performance that anyone over 50 could fly on their very first try.\nBut the big drone companies fought back. The price of military-spec stabilization components made the project seem economically impossible. Suppliers backed out after pressure from major manufacturers. One parts distributor cancelled their order the day before shipping after receiving a call from a "concerned competitor."\nAfter this setback, Marcus went back to the drawing board. He realized they didn''t need to match military costs ‚Äî they needed to reverse-engineer how consumer drones failed and build something completely different from scratch.\nAfter nearly three years of prototyping, testing with focus groups of retirees, and redesigning the controls seventeen times, Marcus cracked it.\nHe miniaturized the same triple-axis gyroscopic stabilization used in classified military operations. He sourced whisper-silent brushless motors from a covert military supplier ‚Äî the same motors used in reconnaissance drones where any sound could get soldiers killed. And he designed a controller with large, tactile buttons and a bright screen specifically for adult hands and eyes.\nThe result is that you get military-grade drone footage from your backyard for a tiny fraction of what the big companies charge. And it''s very easy to set up:\nUnbox the Ghost Wing and charge it for 30 minutes.\nHold the controller and press the green button.\nWatch the drone rise smoothly and hover in place, steady as a statue.\nPoint the joystick where you want it to go and watch your TV fill up with stunning aerial footage.\nAnd if you ever lose sight of it ‚Äî flew it too far, over the trees, around the house ‚Äî just press the red button. Ghost Wing navigates itself back to you automatically. Every single time.\nWant to let your spouse try? Hand them the controller. Want to bring it to your son''s house for Thanksgiving? Slip it in your bag. It''s the size of a water bottle.\nThe best part is the reinforced polymer frame has a tested lifespan of over five years of regular use, survives crashes onto concrete, and the stabilization software updates automatically so your footage keeps getting smoother.\nMany experts predicted a drone with this technology would cost two thousand dollars or more. But Marcus didn''t create Ghost Wing to compete with luxury gadgets for tech enthusiasts.\nHe created it for his brother-in-law. For retirees who want to capture memories without fighting a machine. For grandparents who are tired of feeling left behind by technology designed to confuse them.\nThat''s why he priced it at just 200 dollars.\nBut it gets better.\nGhost Wing is currently running a new customer promotion that lets you get one for only 99 dollars ‚Äî fifty percent off.\nAnd it comes with a no-questions-asked 90-day money-back guarantee. Fly it for three full months. Crash it. Test it in wind. Let your grandkids try it. If you don''t love it ‚Äî if your footage doesn''t make your family ask "how did you do that?" ‚Äî send it back for a complete refund.\nBut supplies are limited. The specialized silent motors come from a single factory and production is capped. The last four shipments sold out in 72 hours.\nVisit the official link below to check if Ghost Wing is still in stock at the discounted price.\nYou spent your whole life working. Building. Sacrificing.\nYou''ve earned the right to capture what matters ‚Äî without feeling like technology left you behind.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1024, '2026-01-11T18:50:20.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recTkxwxaBkRJoIgH', 'GhostWing - Script 1073 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('A 78-year-old grandmother just flew a military drone on her very first try ‚Äî no manual, no help from anyone. When did we decide that everyone over 55 needs a 30-page manual and a YouTube tutorial just to fly a drone? One US Army engineer said "enough" ‚Äî and built the drone she used.\n\nBig drone companies have been selling complicated, overpriced machines for years. Half of them end up in a closet after one frustrating afternoon. You spent $400, crashed it into a tree, and never touched it again. Maybe you sat through a tutorial that made you feel stupid. None of that is your fault. Those drones were never designed for you. DJI builds for tech reviewers, not regular people. Your grandson shouldn''t have to be your permanent tech support just so you can see your own roof.\n\nThat changes today. Captain Adam Scott, a 44-year-old US Army officer and leading engineer, was assigned to develop advanced optical equipment for US Special Forces. His team needed to capture enemy positions from miles away during a critical mission in the Middle East ‚Äî operating in terrain where a single detection meant mission failure. After months of classified research, they created a breakthrough prototype. It became the most celebrated military invention in recent years ‚Äî the first device ever built with patented MOT military optical technology. That means it''s at least 20 times more powerful than any drone you can buy in a store, capturing everything in stunning 4K from tens of miles away.\n\nAdam saw what this could do for regular people ‚Äî especially the millions who gave up on drones because every option felt like it required an engineering degree. So he secured every permission needed, redesigned it for everyday use, and readied it for mass production. He called it GhostWing, and it''s the most powerful yet simplest drone ever made.\n\nGhostWing uses military-grade carbon-polymer construction with custom software that increases power and control by 120%% ‚Äî it flies itself and you just point where you want it to go. One tap on your phone and it rises, steadies, and starts recording. The "follow me" feature tracks you automatically ‚Äî no piloting skill needed, no controller required. The advanced GPS locks your location within 900 meters, so this drone cannot get lost ‚Äî it comes back on its own when the signal weakens or the battery dips. The collision detection system makes it impossible to crash, even on your very first flight. The 4K camera captures footage so sharp that professional photographers are switching to GhostWing from rigs costing ten times as much. It folds smaller than a water bottle, flies 70%% quieter than competitors, covers 2.7 miles, and stays airborne for 15 full minutes. Completely waterproof. Virtually indestructible.\n\nPicture this: you press one button, watch GhostWing rise above your house, and suddenly your phone shows a crystal-clear view of your entire roof ‚Äî no ladder, no $300 inspection fee. Next weekend you''re filming your grandkids from angles that look like a Hollywood movie. On vacation, you''re capturing memories your family will watch for decades.\n\nWhen Adam first launched GhostWing, it spread through the military community overnight. Then everyday people started posting their footage online and it went viral. Celebrities, professional photographers, and filmmakers all made the switch. It holds 4.9 stars across 15,000 reviews. Tag someone over 55 who deserves to finally own a drone that actually respects their time.\n\nIt already sold out once in 48 hours. Adam has tripled production and is offering a 50%% discount ‚Äî GhostWing for just $99 ‚Äî but only for orders placed in the next 24 hours. At this price, this batch won''t last either. Every unit ships with a 30-day money-back guarantee. Order multiple and the discounts stack ‚Äî the perfect gift for anyone who deserved a better drone years ago. Click below to claim your 50%% off before this deal is pulled.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1073, '2026-02-18T17:24:55.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recU8XmMyJWv33owc', 'GhostWing - Script 1038 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('I almost didn''t buy this $99 military drone because the price seemed too cheap to be real. Then my daughter started crying when she saw what it captured at my grandson''s birthday party.\n\nLet me tell you how a 73-year-old man ended up with the same technology the US Special Forces use.\n\nGhostWing was created specifically for Special Forces missions by Captain Adam Scott, a 44-year-old US Army officer and lead engineer. He and his team spent 11 years developing classified optical equipment for critical operations in the Middle East. The mission required photographing enemy positions from miles away without ever being detected.\n\nThey created a breakthrough prototype. The Pentagon celebrated it as the most successful military invention in recent years. It was the first to ever use the patented MOT military optical technology, meaning it''s at least 20 times more powerful than any drone at Best Buy.\n\nIt can literally capture anything from miles away with stunning 4K quality.\n\nWhen Adam retired, he rebuilt this technology for regular people like me. He called it GhostWing.\n\nHere''s why I could use it even though I can barely work my television remote.\n\nAdam developed software that increases power and control by 120%%, making it so easy that literally anyone can fly it. My 6-year-old granddaughter had it in the air on her second try.\n\nAt Tommy''s birthday party, I tapped the "Follow Me" button. For 45 minutes, GhostWing followed the kids around the backyard capturing everything automatically. The three-legged race. The water balloon fight. The look on Tommy''s face opening presents.\n\nMy daughter watched the footage that night and burst into tears. She said it looked like we hired a professional film crew. The whole party cost me less than what I used to pay for disposable cameras and developing at the drugstore.\n\nGhostWing uses military-grade nanotechnology and composite materials‚Äîsame quality as professional setups costing thousands. The GPS tracks within 900 meters and returns automatically if signal drops. Collision detection prevents any crash or damage.\n\nIt''s virtually indestructible. Completely waterproof. Handles any temperature.\n\nWhen GhostWing launched, it spread like wildfire in the military community. Then videos started going viral everywhere. It sold out within 48 hours and developed a waitlist of over 10,000 orders. Professional photographers and filmmakers have made the switch to it.\n\nCaptain Scott has tripled production and is offering a 50%% discount for anyone who orders within the next 24 hours. You can get even deeper discounts by ordering multiple GhostWings.\n\nMy advice: grab one for yourself and a few more for your friends and family. Take it from someone who thought he was too old for this stuff. Click on the link below this video to visit the official website and order with 50%% off.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1038, '2026-01-18T08:51:28.000Z');
