one''s power and control by 120%%, making it so easy to operate that anyone can use it. It''s loaded with cutting edge technology like the Follow Me feature, which lets you take amazing videos of yourself without even touching the control. The advanced GPS functionality means it can track your location within 900 meters and return to you quickly when experiencing a weak or when the battery is low. The collision detection function prevents any accidental crash or damage, making this drone the safest quadcopter ever engineered. And because it''s made of the best military materials available, it''s virtually indestructible.\n\n\nIt''s completely waterproof and strong enough to withstand both freezing and scorching hot temperatures. And what''s best about this drone is that you can use it for thousands of different purposes. Whether you''re excited about turning your social media profile into a viral sensation or you want to capture precious memories with your family, the possibilities with the GhostWing are endless. It''s also a perfect security tool, allowing you to spot anything from a safe distance. When Adam first launched GhostWing, it spread like wildfire in the military community.\n\n\nWhat he didn''t expect was for everyone to start sharing all over the internet the incredible footage they shot with the GhostWing. After going viral, it sold out within the first 48 hours and quickly developed a waitlist of over 10,000 orders from all around the world. Celebrities, professional photographers, and filmmakers all made the switch to it. Adam wants everyone to know about this new technology, so he has since tripled the production and is offering a 50 %% discount for anyone who orders it within the next 24 hours. You can get even more discounts by ordering multiple GhostWings making it a perfect gift for anyone. My advice, grab one for yourself and more for your friends and family before this amazing deal is taken down. Click on the link below this video to visit the official website and order with 50 %% off.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1006, '2025-12-18T22:06:06.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recW2gLLTELax2Gf7', 'GhostWing - Script 1071 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('My 82-year-old dad called me last night. "Son, get over here right now." I thought something was wrong. I rushed over and found him in the backyard, flying a drone over his garden, grinning like a kid on Christmas morning. An 82-year-old man who still can''t figure out Netflix was flying a military-grade drone with one finger. And that''s when I knew everything I believed about drones was dead wrong.\n\nBecause here''s the truth nobody talks about. Millions of Americans over 55 have bought drones. Expensive ones. DJI, Autel, brands that cost $400, $800, even $1,200. And every single one of those drones is sitting in a closet right now. Collecting dust. Because the apps are confusing, the controllers look like a fighter jet cockpit, and one wrong move sends your $800 investment straight into a tree. You''ve watched the YouTube tutorials. You''ve handed the controller to your grandson and said "you fly it." But deep down you feel like this technology just wasn''t built for you.\n\nIt wasn''t. Until now.\n\nBecause a 44-year-old US Army officer named Captain Adam Scott built something different. He and his team were assigned to develop cutting-edge optical equipment for a critical Special Forces mission in the Middle East. The mission required capturing enemy positions from miles away without ever being detected. After months of research, they created a breakthrough prototype that became the most celebrated military invention in recent years. It was the first device to ever use the patented MOT military optical technology, making it at least 20 times more powerful than any commercially available drone with stunning 4K image quality.\n\nAfter seeing what this technology could do, Adam realized something. If a soldier under enemy fire could operate this drone with zero training, why couldn''t a retired schoolteacher in Ohio do the same thing from a lawn chair? So he secured every permission needed, redesigned the device for everyday Americans, and called it GhostWing.\n\nGhostWing is the most powerful drone ever made and the easiest one to fly. Adam developed software that increases power and control by 120 percent, which means the drone practically flies itself. You just point where you want it to go. The "follow me" feature lets you capture stunning video of yourself without touching a single button, no piloting skill needed whatsoever. The advanced GPS tracks your location within 900 meters and brings the drone back to you automatically when the signal weakens or the battery gets low. It literally cannot get lost. The collision detection system prevents any crash or damage, making it impossible to wreck even on your very first flight. Built from military-grade carbon-polymer materials, it''s waterproof, survives freezing winters and scorching summers, and folds smaller than a water bottle. It flies 70 percent quieter than competitors with a 2.7-mile range and 15 minutes of flight time.\n\nPicture this. You press one button. GhostWing rises straight up. Suddenly your phone shows a crystal-clear view of your entire roof, every shingle, every gutter, no ladder, no $300 inspection fee. Your grandkids run across the yard and GhostWing follows them automatically, capturing footage you''ll watch a thousand times. You survey your whole property line in minutes. You check on your home security from the couch. On vacation, you capture memories that look like a Hollywood movie.\n\nWhen Adam first launched GhostWing, it spread like wildfire through military families. Then the videos hit the internet. Retired couples filming their lake houses. Grandparents capturing family reunions from the sky. Tag someone over 60 who needs to see this. GhostWing earned 4.9 stars from over 15,000 reviews, sold out in 48 hours, and built a waitlist of 10,000 orders worldwide.\n\nAdam has tripled production and is offering 50 percent off for anyone who orders in the next 24 hours, bringing it down to just $99. Order multiple GhostWings for even bigger discounts, backed by a 30-day guarantee. Grab one for yourself and one for every person in your family who deserves to finally enjoy this technology. Click the link below to visit the official site and order at 50 percent off before this deal disappears.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1071, '2026-02-18T17:24:25.000Z');
