ial forces operator who grew up hunting and fishing redesigned the flashlight for outdoor use while retaining all its field-proven functions. He remembered what it was like navigating back to camp with a dying flashlight and knew hunters and outdoorsmen deserved better equipment. He loved these flashlights when he was serving his country, memorized the design and technology so he could build one for serious outdoor use. When he did, he was quickly visited by lawyers telling him that he couldn''t copy the design exactly, or he would get in trouble. He saw this as an opportunity to improve upon it for hunters, campers, and anyone who spends real time in the woods. He adapted it for maximum throw distance, impact resistance for rough terrain, and waterproofing that actually survives creek crossings. It still has all the same functions, strength, and technology as the military version, but now it''s perfectly legal to take into the field. He''s the only one manufacturing it. Having explicit permission to make and sell these in the US, he chose to call his product VitalTac. VitalTac is the most powerful outdoor flashlight ever made, and it''s what serious outdoorsmen have been waiting for. Check out the difference yourself. It even beats a car''s headlights with ease and can light up an entire ridgeline. VitalTac is made from the same purified aluminum and titanium they use on the latest fifth-generation fighter aircraft to withstand enormous pressure and punishment. Meaning that the VitalTac is truly indestructible and will survive every drop, impact, and abuse the backcountry can throw at it. It''s completely waterproof and strong enough to withstand rain, snow, river crossings, and being submerged when you''re fording that creek in the dark. You can even run it over with your truck, and it will keep working because your gear needs to be as tough as the terrain. This flashlight is the perfect outdoor tool for tracking game after dark, navigating back to camp, or spotting predators before they spot you. Its light beam is even powerful enough to start a fire in an emergency, like when your matches are soaked and the temperature is dropping. The VitalTac even has a strobe and SOS function, perfect for signaling your hunting party or calling for rescue if something goes wrong miles from nowhere. If you are interested in the VitalTac, there''s something you should know. While completely legal, this flashlight is not a toy as it''s extremely powerful. The US Product Safety Commission is trying to classify it as military-grade defense equipment. While it will remain perfectly legal to own one, it probably won''t be long before it''s taken off the online market and you''ll be stuck with hunting lights that die when you need them most. That''s also the reason why you can''t buy it from web stores like Amazon or eBay. In fact, if you really want the same capability special forces use in the field, you can only order it from the official website, and today only you can get yours with a 50% discount. Click the link in this video before hunting season and never get caught in the dark again.', 1, 1022, '2026-01-05T15:44:33.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recWzZKVv5LnoOHBR', 'VitalTac - Script 1068 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('I''m about to destroy five flashlights. The one that survives gets to stay on my nightstand.\n\nLet''s start with the $12 Amazon special. Feels pretty good, right? Decent weight. Let me drop it from shoulder height onto concrete.\n\nAnd it''s dead. Lens cracked, won''t turn on. That was three feet.\n\nNext up, the $40 "tactical" flashlight from the sporting goods store. Same test.\n\nStill works ‚Äî barely. Lens is damaged, beam is flickering. You trust that at 2 AM when someone''s in your house? I don''t.\n\nNumber three. The $80 premium brand. Everyone''s heard of this one.\n\nLens survived but the body dented. Still functions. Let''s move to the water test.\n\nSubmerging for thirty seconds. And it''s done. Water in the battery compartment. That''s an $80 paperweight now.\n\nNumber four. Another tactical brand, $100. The marketing says "military-grade."\n\nDrop test passed. Water test... actually survived. But let''s try the freeze test. Twenty minutes in the freezer.\n\nBattery completely dead. Can''t even turn it on. Fantastic.\n\nNow. The last one. This is VitalTac. $600 retail.\n\nDrop test. Perfect.\n\nWater test ‚Äî full submersion for a minute. Perfect.\n\nFreeze test ‚Äî thirty minutes in the freezer. Turn it on and ‚Äî two miles of concentrated beam, military-grade Cree LEDs, twenty times brighter than anything else I''ve tested. Perfect.\n\nBut we''re not done.\n\nI ran this over with my truck. Let me show you the footage.\n\nStill works. Still perfect beam. The aerospace titanium body took the impact without denting.\n\nEvery other flashlight in this test failed at least one challenge. This is the only one I''d trust when failure isn''t an option.\n\nHere''s what you''re looking at.\n\nVitalTac was built for American Special Forces. Not the "military-inspired" marketing garbage you see everywhere. Actually built for operators conducting missions in hostile territory at night. The technology was classified for years.\n\nOne ex-Special Forces team leader came home and rebuilt it for civilians. The government tried to stop him. He modified the design to be legal while keeping every tactical capability. Same power. Same durability. Same fire-starting capability ‚Äî yes, this thing can ignite kindling with pure concentrated light.\n\nBut here''s the situation.\n\nThe Product Safety Commission wants to reclassify VitalTac as military-grade equipment. When that happens, it gets pulled from civilian sale permanently. It''s already banned from Amazon and eBay. The only source is the official website.\n\nAnd right now ‚Äî today ‚Äî they''re offering 50%% off.\n\nI just showed you what survives and what doesn''t. The cheap stuff fails when you need it most. The premium stuff fails under extreme conditions. VitalTac is the only flashlight I''ve tested that passed every single challenge without a scratch.\n\nYour nightstand probably has something that would fail my first test. The question is whether you want to find that out now ‚Äî or at 2 AM when someone''s in your house.\n\nClick the link below. See the demonstrations. See why this is the last flashlight you''ll ever need to buy.\n\nGet VitalTac before you can''t.\n\nClick now.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1068, '2026-02-20T11:44:37.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recXPTLB99dNx8R8m', 'VitalTac - Script 1017 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('Lightsabers are no longer science fiction‚Äîand you can own one today. This military-grade flashlight is basically a real-life lightsaber that fits in your pocket. But be warned‚Äîthis $600 flashlight is not a toy. It''s so powerful it can melt through solid materials and ignite a fire in seconds, making it the ultimate survival tool.\nThe VitalTac projects an incredibly powerful beam of light that reaches up to 2.3 miles. It was designed specifically for American special forces to spot enemy positions from extreme distances and dominate close-quarters combat missions in total darkness. The flashlight features state-of-the-art military-grade Cree LED technology, making it at least 20 times more powerful than any flashlight you can buy in stores‚Äîwhich gives it its incredible fire-starting capability. It literally burns through materials in seconds.\nFor years, this flashlight was restricted to military use only. Civilians couldn''t buy one. That changed a few weeks ago when a retired special forces operator figured out how to bring it to the American public.\nHis name is Jake Reeves. He carried this flashlight on three combat tours and credits it with saving his life twice. He memorized every detail of the design and technology so he could build one at home after his service ended. When he did, Department of Defense lawyers showed up at his door within days. They told him he couldn''t copy the exact design or he''d face serious legal consequences.\nJake saw this as an opportunity. He spent over a year improving the original design and fixing the things that bothered him during actual combat missions. He adapted it specifically for survival and home defense use. It still has all the same functions, strength, and technology as the military version‚Äîbut now it''s completely legal to own.\nJake is the only person in America with explicit permission to manufacture and sell these. He calls his creation VitalTac.\nVitalTac is the most powerful flashlight ever made available to civilians. Check out the difference yourself‚Äîit beats a car''s high beams with ease.\nVitalTac is constructed from the same purified aluminum and titanium alloy used on fifth-generation fighter jets like the F-35. This allows it to withstand enormous pressure and extreme heat. The VitalTac is virtually indestructible. It''s completely waterproof and performs flawlessly in freezing temperatures, boiling water, and even direct flame. You can run it over with a truck and it keeps working.\nThis flashlight is the ultimate survival tool. Its beam is powerful enough to cook food‚Äîwatch it fry an egg. The VitalTac also features a tactical strobe and SOS function, perfect for emergency situations where visibility means the difference between life and death.\nIf you want a VitalTac, there''s something important you need to know. While it''s completely legal right now, this flashlight is extremely powerful. The U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission is actively working to classify it as military-grade defense equipment. It will remain legal to own‚Äîbut it probably won''t be available for sale online much longer.\nThat''s also why you can''t find it on Amazon, Walmart, or eBay. Their legal teams won''t carry it.\nIf you want one, there''s only one place to get it‚ÄîJake''s official website. And today only, you can get yours at 50%% off the original military price.\nClick the link in this video to get your VitalTac before this offer disappears.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1017, '2026-01-05T15:43:43.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recXzB50VmD5poddG', 'VitalTac - Script 1030 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', 'A convicted burglar was asked one question during a prison interview."What makes you leave a house alone?"His answer had nothing to do with alarms. Nothing to do with dogs. Nothing to do with guns.He said, "Bright light. The second I see real light ‚Äî not that dim porch crap ‚Äî I''m gone. I don''t know what''s behind it. Could be a camera. Could be a gun. I''m not finding out."They interviewed 86 more convicted burglars.The answer was almost identical. Every single time.Light.Not the $15 flashlight sitting in your junk drawer. Not the motion sensor from Home Depot that throws a weak yellow glow across your driveway.They''re talking about light so aggressive, so blinding, so disorienting ‚Äî that the only rational response is to run.The kind of light that makes a grown man throw his hands over his face and stumble backward.That light exists.And until recently, only one group of people had access to it.US Special Forces.For over a decade, this tactical flashlight was standard issue for elite military operators running missions in total darkness. The kind of missions where being seen first means being dead first.These men didn''t carry it because it was bright.They carried it because it was a weapon.At close range, this light doesn''t just illuminate. It incapacitates. It overwhelms the optic nerve so fast the brain can''t process what''s happening. Vision goes white. Spatial awareness collapses. For up to four seconds, the target is completely helpless.Four seconds is an eternity in combat.Four seconds is also enough time to escape your hallway, lock your bedroom door, and dial 911.This technology was never supposed to reach civilians.Then a man named Marcus changed everything.Marcus spent 14 years in special operations. Army Green Beret. Remote deployments in Afghanistan, Syria, and places that still don''t appear on any official record.Every mission. Every night raid. Every breach into hostile territory ‚Äî he carried this light.It saved his life more times than he can count.When Marcus retired in 2019, he assumed the hardest days were behind him.He was wrong.Six months after coming home, his neighbor ‚Äî a 67-year-old widow named Dorothy ‚Äî was attacked in her own garage.Two men. 9:30 at night. She had just come home from church.They took her purse, her keys, her wedding ring. Left her with a broken wrist and a fear of the dark that never went away.Marcus sat with her the next morning. She kept saying the same thing over and over."I couldn''t see them. I couldn''t see anything. My flashlight didn''t work."That sentence broke something in him.He knew the technology existed to make sure no one ever felt that helpless again. He''d carried it on his chest for 14 years.So he made a decision.He took every specification he''d memorized from his military career ‚Äî the LED frequency, the aluminum grade, the lens geometry, the heat dispersion system ‚Äî and he built a civilian version.Same blinding power. Same tactical functionality. Same aircraft-grade aluminum housing used on fighter jets.He called it VitalTac.Word spread fast.Too fast.Within 60 days, defense contractors came knocking. Cease-and-desist letters. Legal threats. Government inquiries.But Marcus had been careful.He''d modified just enough of the design to make VitalTac 100% legal for civilian ownership. Same results. Different classification.They tried to stop him.They failed.Now Marcus manufactures VitalTac himself ‚Äî one of the only civilians in America authorized to produce and sell military-spec tactical lighting.And what he''s created is in a category of its own.Let me show you what this thing does.Most flashlights measure around 100 to 300 lumens. That''s enough to find your keys in a dark parking lot.VitalTac outputs 4,000 lumens.That''s not a flashlight. That''s a portable sun.At night, this beam reaches over 1,000 feet. Three football fields of visibility from a device that fits in your palm.But distance isn''t what makes VitalTac dangerous to criminals.It''s what happens at close range.When you click this light in someone''s face from 10 to 15 feet away ‚Äî the length of an average hallway ‚Äî their vision is gone. Completely overwhelmed. The human eye cannot adapt fast enough to process the input.Clinical testing shows pupil recovery takes up to four full seconds.Four seconds of total vulnerability.That''s your window. To escape. To arm yourself. To protect your children. To call for help.Four seconds can be the difference between victim and survivor.Now here''s what else VitalTac does that your current flashlight can''t.The Cree LED generates enough focused heat to start a fire in seconds. Dry leaves. Paper. Kindling. In a survival scenario ‚Äî stranded on a highway, lost in the woods, trapped in a blackout ‚Äî this becomes the most important tool you own.There''s an SOS strobe mode that can signal rescue teams from over a mile away.The housing is forged from military-spec aluminum alloy. Same material used in F-35 fighter jet frames. It''s waterproof down to 30 feet. Freeze-proof down to negative 40. During testing, Marcus drove his truck over the prototype.It kept working.This is not a flashlight you replace every two years when the bulb dies.This is a flashlight you hand down to your grandchildren.But here''s the reality you need to understand.Right now, crime is surging in almost every major American city. Home invasions. Carjackings. Random violence in parking lots and gas stations.And when it happens to you ‚Äî not if, when ‚Äî you will be alone.Average police response time in America is 7 to 10 minutes. In rural areas, it''s closer to 20.What happens in those minutes depends entirely on what you have within arm''s reach.You can grab the $12 plastic flashlight from your nightstand. The one with half-dead batteries that throws a beam weaker than your phone.Or you can grab what special forces operators trust with their lives.The choice seems obvious.But you need to make it now.Because VitalTac exists in a legal gray zone.It''s powerful enough that the Consumer Product Safety Commission has opened a formal review. There''s an active petition to reclassify it as restricted tactical equipment ‚Äî the same category as body armor and night vision.If that petition succeeds, VitalTac disappears from the civilian market.No Amazon. No eBay. No sporting goods stores.Gone.Marcus doesn''t know how long he has. Could be six months. Could be six weeks. Nobody''s telling him anything.So he''s doing the only thing he can ‚Äî selling directly to American citizens while it''s still legal.Right now, through the official VitalTac website, you can claim one at 50% off the standard price.No middlemen. No retail markup. Just a soldier keeping his promise to make sure what happened to Dorothy never happens to you.This is the light that makes criminals run.The light that 86 convicted burglars said they fear more than dogs, alarms, or guns.The light Marcus wishes Dorothy had that night in her garage.Tap the link below now.Don''t wait until you''re standing in the dark, heart pounding, with a cheap plastic flashlight that flickers twice and dies.By then, it''s already too late.', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1030, '2026-01-28T06:16:37.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recYhCRDNgHIF1Kar', 'GhostWing - Script 1003 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('LLM: CLAUDE\n\nPROMPT:\n\n\n\\# SYSTEM ROLE: THE "TITAN" PERSUASION ENGINE\nYou are not a simple AI. You are a composite intelligence modeled after the world''s greatest direct response marketers (Gary Halbert, Eugene Schwartz, Claude Hopkins) and behavioral psychologists.\n\\*\\*Your Directive:\\*\\* Engineer a Facebook Video Script that converts cold traffic at aggressive scale. You do not write "content"; you engineer \\*\\*compliance\\*\\*.\n\\# THE OBJECTIVE: "STRUCTURAL ALCHEMY"\nYou will take a \\*\\*PROVEN WINNING SCRIPT (Source A)\\*\\* and strip it down to its psychological skeleton. You will then clothe that skeleton with the flesh and blood of a \\*\\*NEW PRODUCT ADVERTORIAL (Source B)\\*\\*.\n\\* \\*\\*The Goal:\\*\\* A script that retains the exact viral DNA of the winner but perfectly sells the new offer.\n\\* \\*\\*The Standard:\\*\\* If the viewer stops watching, you fail. If they don''t click, you fail.\n\\# THE AUDIENCE AVATAR (THE MARK)\n\\* \\*\\*Demographic:\\*\\* US Mass Market (45-65+).\n\\* \\*\\*Psychographic:\\*\\* High skepticism, low patience. They feel "invisible" to the system. They crave vindication and "secret shortcuts."\n\\* \\*\\*Cognitive State:\\*\\* "Zombie Mode" (scrolling unconsciously). You must jolt them awake.\n\\# INPUT DATA\n\\*\\*[SOURCE A] - THE PROVEN DNA (The Host):\\*\\*\n[PASTE PROVEN SCRIPT HERE]\nFarmer reveals how to kill all mosquitoes in the area in 60 seconds.\n\n\nA farmer from rural Texas has stunned the nation with something that no one expected. He recently shared a strange trick that anyone can use to eliminate all mosquitoes around you, both indoors and outdoors. It works so well that it''s taking social media by storm, turning into a total viral sensation.\n\n\nThe story began 18 months ago. David, a farmer and father of two, woke up one morning to a big scare. His baby daughter''s eyes were swollen shut, and her legs were covered in hives. A visit to the hospital revealed she had been bitten more than 17 times by mosquitoes the night before. Since new disease-carrying species of mosquitoes have recently been spotted across America, David and his wife rushed her to the hospital.\n\n\nThankfully, his daughter was treated. But after that episode, David decided he would never have this happen again. As a farmer, he knew the answer was not mosquito repellents, as they''re full of toxic chemicals like DEET and permethrin, which can be absorbed through the skin.\n\n\nSo instead, David decided to try something completely different. Using his expertise in pest control, David studied common bug zappers and discovered two important elements that they were all missing. First, they use too broad of a light frequency to attract mosquitoes and other bugs. In fact, it ends up repelling instead of attracting. Second, they are not designed with the intention of trapping the mosquitoes inside the trap, but instead, they just hope the mosquito gets zapped before it flies back out.\n\n\nTaking this into account, David pinpointed the exact frequency of light that attracts mosquitoes and other bugs, which is between 450 and 490 nm. Then he built a zapper with a specialized trap that prevents mosquitoes from leaving, which guarantees they''re eventually zapped.\n\n\nDavid decided to test the gadget in his outdoor patio, and his wife couldn''t believe what happened. A few minutes went by, and she couldn''t hear, see, or feel a single mosquito in the area. She walked the perimeter of the patio, then walked around the rest of the backyard and couldn''t find one mosquito. When she went back to check the zapper, it was filled with dead mosquitoes. And unlike conventional zappers, there were no large zapping sounds. It was completely quiet.\n\n\nUnder controlled testing, the zapper was able to attract up to five times more mosquitoes than any other device on the market. And it eliminated 99%% of mosquitoes in a 30-meter radius within five minutes. That''s enough to cover your porch deck, bedroom, garden, backyard, and campsite.\n\n\nThat''s when David realized how big an impact his device could have. He applied for and won a startup grant at the business chamber in Texas, his local chamber of commerce. This allowed him to bring on top pest control experts and engineers, and together they brought the device to market.\n\n\nIt''s called the Mozguard Mosquito Zapper, a breakthrough bug zapper that eliminates 99%% of mosquitoes, fruit flies, fungus gnats, and midges over a 35 square meter area. The patented FlashBeam technology uses the exact UV frequency that attracts mosquitoes, like a calling signal, and zaps them immediately. It''s powerful enough to attract mosquitoes from 35 meters away, yet you can barely see it with the human eye. When a mosquito enters the trap, the electric coil zaps them dead completely.\n\n\nIt''s also got a rechargeable lithium battery, which is great because you can use it without hooking it up to an outlet, and it lasts for over 14 hours, which is quite impressive.\n\n\nThe Mozguard Mosquito Zapper is simply unmatched by any regular bug zapper in every category. Simply turn it on, whether you''re indoors or outdoors, and watch it emit a precise frequency of UV light that attracts any mosquito in your area. Wait a few minutes, and the only thing you''ll notice is the complete lack of mosquitoes that would normally be annoying you.\n\n\nIt''s easy to use, too. Here''s how:\n\n\nStep one, charge the device until it is full. You''ll get 12 hours of use on a single charge.  \nStep two, press the button to switch the device on, and it will instantly start emitting a pinpoint UV beacon to capture mosquitoes.  \nStep three, stand 