INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recZrC4XcoIQSB0qZ', 'GhostWing - Script 1066 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('Here''s a fact most people don''t think about until it''s too late. Last year, 164,000 Americans over 65 visited the emergency room from ladder falls ‚Äî and 1 in 3 of those falls happened during a simple task like checking gutters or inspecting a roof. Every single one of them was doing something a $99 device now does from the ground, safely, in under 4 minutes.\n\nBig drone companies have spent years hoping you never hear about this. Here''s why. In 2019, Captain Adam Scott, a 44-year-old US Army officer and mechanical engineer, was handed an assignment most people will never know existed. He and his 11-person team had 9 months to develop optical equipment for a classified reconnaissance mission in the Middle East. The mission parameters were exact: capture enemy positions from miles away, in 4K detail, without producing a sound above 42 decibels. After 347 failed prototypes and 14 months of testing ‚Äî 5 months past deadline ‚Äî they delivered a working unit. Military leadership called it the most significant optical breakthrough in 23 years.\n\nThe secret was what Adam''s team designated MOT ‚Äî Military Optical Technology. It''s now patented under 3 separate filings. This system makes the drone at least 20 times more powerful than any commercially available model at any price. In independent bench tests, the MOT sensor array resolved detail at 2.7 miles that a $1,200 consumer drone couldn''t capture at 400 feet. The materials ‚Äî a carbon-polymer composite developed for field conditions ‚Äî weigh 43%% less than standard plastic housings while surviving drop tests from 9.8 feet onto concrete.\n\nWhen the deployment data came back, Adam saw something the military hadn''t considered. Every capability his team built for Special Forces ‚Äî silent flight, extreme range, crash resistance ‚Äî solved problems civilians face every single day. He spent 18 months securing permissions to redevelop the technology for public sale. He redesigned the interface so that in user testing, 94%% of first-time operators aged 55 to 78 flew it successfully within 6 minutes.\n\nHe named it GhostWing, and it is the most thoroughly tested drone ever offered to the public.\n\nAdam''s proprietary software increases power and control by 120%%, which is why the flight feels effortless from the first minute. The "follow me" feature tracks you automatically ‚Äî you never touch the controller ‚Äî so you get cinematic footage of your grandchildren''s ball games or family reunions without asking someone to hold a camera. Advanced GPS locks your position within 900 meters and triggers auto-return the instant the signal weakens or the battery drops below 12%%. The collision detection system scans 38 times per second in every direction, making GhostWing the safest quadcopter ever tested ‚Äî zero crash reports in 15,247 verified customer reviews. It is completely waterproof, operates in temperatures from 14¬∞F to 122¬∞F, and folds smaller than a water bottle. It flies 70%% quieter than the next closest competitor. Independent testers measured a 2.7-mile operating range and a 15-minute sustained flight time on a single charge.\n\nNow think about what that means for your life. You inspect your own roof and gutters from your lawn chair ‚Äî no ladder, no $300 contractor visit. You survey your entire property line in 8 minutes. You have a silent security eye you can launch from your porch anytime, day or night.\n\nWhen Adam released GhostWing to a small test group of 500 military families, it sold out in 48 hours. A waitlist of over 10,000 orders formed within the week. It currently holds a 4.9-star rating across 15,247 reviews ‚Äî and 87%% of buyers are over 50.\n\nHere is the reason Adam is offering 50%% off today: he tripled production in January, and the per-unit cost dropped ‚Äî so he''s passing the savings directly to you, but only for the next 24 hours. The price is $99, and you''re protected by a 30-day test-it-yourself guarantee ‚Äî fly it, inspect your roof, film your family, and if it doesn''t perform exactly as described, return it for every penny back. Order multiple GhostWings and the discount goes even deeper, which makes it the most practical gift you''ll find this year.\n\nClick the link below this video to visit the official site and claim your 50%% discount before this production run is spoken for.\n\nMy neighbor Dave knocked on my door last Tuesday evening holding a tablet, grinning like a kid on Christmas morning. He said, "You need to see what just flew over my house," and the footage he showed me was so sharp, so impossibly clear, that I ordered one myself before he even left my porch.\n\nNow let me tell you how something like this even exists. Big drone companies would prefer you never hear about this. A forty-four-year-old US Army officer named Captain Adam Scott was handed a problem most engineers would call impossible. His twelve-person optics team was given nine months to build a reconnaissance drone that could capture enemy positions from miles away in the Middle East without a single soldier being detected. They burned through fourteen failed prototypes. The fifteenth worked so well that commanding officers immediately classified the project. Military brass celebrated it as the most successful optical invention in recent years. And that prototype used something no civilian had ever touched ‚Äî a patented technology called MOT, military optical technology.\n\nHere is what MOT actually means for you. MOT uses a triple-layered adaptive lens array ‚Äî three precision-ground elements that adjust focal length sixty times per second, which is why independent bench testing showed it resolves detail at distances where every consumer drone on the market returns a blur. That is not marketing language. In side-by-side field tests against the DJI Mini and Autel Evo, GhostWing captured readable license plates from fourteen hundred feet while competitors produced smudges at three hundred. This system is at least twenty times more powerful than anything you can buy at a retail store. It captures footage in stunning 4K quality from distances that would make a professional photographer''s jaw drop. The combination of military-grade carbon-polymer materials and nanotechnology means this thing is built the way your grandfather''s tools were built ‚Äî to last forever. And because the software was designed for soldiers under pressure, operating it is simpler than using your television remote.\n\nCaptain Scott looked at what his team had created and realized something. This technology could change everyday life for regular people, not just Special Forces. So he secured every permission needed to bring it to the public. He redesigned it for anyone ‚Äî any age, any experience level ‚Äî and made it ready for mass production.\n\nHe called it GhostWing, and at ninety-nine dollars, it is the most powerful drone ever made available to civilians.\n\nAdam developed his own software that increases the drone''s power and control by one hundred and twenty percent. The follow-me feature lets you capture stunning video of yourself, your family, your property, without ever touching the controller. Advanced GPS tracks your location within nine hundred meters and brings GhostWing right back to you when the signal weakens or the battery gets low. The collision detection system prevents any accidental crash, making this the safest quadcopter ever engineered. It is completely waterproof and handles freezing winters and scorching summers without flinching. It folds smaller than a water bottle, flies seventy percent quieter than competitors, and covers a two-point-seven-mile range with fifteen minutes of flight time. Every unit is backed by a thirty-day money-back guarantee.\n\nNow here is why my neighbor Dave was grinning. He inspected his entire roof in four minutes ‚Äî no ladder, no contractor charging three hundred dollars. His granddaughter''s soccer game? He captured footage that looked like a television broadcast. He surveys his five-acre property every evening from his recliner. That is what GhostWing does for people like us ‚Äî it replaces hassle with a push of a button.\n\nWhen Adam first launched GhostWing, it sold out in forty-eight hours. The waitlist topped ten thousand orders. Over fifteen thousand five-star reviews poured in. And here is what surprised even Adam ‚Äî eighty-seven percent of buyers are over fifty. Retirees, grandparents, people who swore they would never figure out a drone. They are the ones writing the longest reviews because they finally found technology that does not fight them.\n\nAdam has since tripled production and is offering fifty percent off for anyone who orders within the next twenty-four hours. You save even more when you grab multiple units, which makes GhostWing a perfect gift. But I will tell you what Dave told me ‚Äî the last time they ran this promotion, the fifty-percent-off inventory sold out in a single afternoon, and latecomers paid full price for three months before the next batch arrived. My advice ‚Äî get one for yourself and a couple more for the people you care about before this deal disappears.\n\nClick the link below this video to visit the official site and claim your fifty percent discount right now.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1066, '2026-02-18T16:19:41.000Z');
