Tap the link now.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1073, '2026-02-20T11:44:41.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('reccMyxnGbA9hZklz', 'GhostWing - Script 1072 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', 'My 76-year-old father spent $900 on a top-rated drone last Christmas and crashed it into a tree 14 seconds after takeoff ‚Äî fourteen seconds and nine hundred dollars, gone. Then I handed him a small $99 military drone, he pressed one button on his phone, and it lifted off his palm and hovered perfectly while he stood there laughing like a kid. Big drone companies don''t want you to see that video because it proves you never needed their expensive, complicated machines. Every year millions of Americans buy drones that end up in closets after one frustrating afternoon. The controllers look like video game remotes with 30 buttons. The apps crash. The YouTube tutorials are 45 minutes long and still don''t help. Your grandson sets it up for you, goes home, and now you''ve got a $900 paperweight you''re too embarrassed to mention. No amount of practice fixes bad design, and DJI''s setup app practically requires an engineering degree. That''s exactly the problem Captain Adam Scott set out to solve. Adam is a 44-year-old US Army officer and leading engineer who was assigned to develop cutting-edge optical equipment for a critical Special Forces mission in the Middle East. His team needed to capture enemy positions from miles away without ever being detected. After months of research they created a groundbreaking prototype that was celebrated as the most successful military invention in recent years. It was the first device to ever use the patented MOT military optical technology, making it at least 20 times more powerful than any commercially available drone. It captures anything from tens of miles away in stunning 4K quality. Adam saw what this could mean for regular people, especially anyone who''d ever been defeated by a complicated drone. So he secured every permission needed to redevelop the device for the public. He called it GhostWing and it is the most powerful drone ever made. GhostWing uses military-grade carbon-polymer and nanotechnology to match the quality of top models at a fraction of the price. Adam''s custom software increases power and control by 120 percent, which means the drone practically flies itself ‚Äî you just point where you want it to go. The follow-me feature films you automatically so no piloting skill is needed at all. Advanced GPS tracks your location within 900 meters and brings the drone back on its own if the signal drops or the battery gets low, so it can never get lost. The collision detection system makes it impossible to crash, even on your very first flight. It folds smaller than a water bottle, flies 70 percent quieter than competitors, covers a 2.7-mile range, and stays airborne for 15 minutes per charge. It is completely waterproof and built to handle freezing cold and scorching heat. Picture this: you press one button, GhostWing lifts off your hand, and suddenly you''re watching your own roof on your phone screen ‚Äî no ladder, no $300 inspector bill. Point it at the grandkids playing in the yard and capture footage that looks like a Hollywood movie. Survey your whole property line in minutes. Set it as a security lookout from your porch. Take it on vacation and finally get those aerial shots you''ve been dreaming about. When Adam first launched GhostWing it spread like wildfire through the military community. Then everyday people started posting their footage online and it exploded. It sold out in 48 hours with a waitlist topping 10,000 orders worldwide. It now holds a 4.9-star rating across more than 15,000 reviews. Celebrities, professional photographers, and filmmakers all made the switch. Tag someone over 55 who deserves to finally fly a drone without stress. Adam has tripled production and is offering a 50 percent discount for anyone who orders within the next 24 hours, backed by a 30-day money-back guarantee. Order multiple GhostWings and the discounts go even deeper, making it a perfect gift. Grab one for yourself and a few more for your family before this deal comes down. Click the link below this video to visit the official website and order your GhostWing at 50 percent off right now.', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1072, '2026-02-18T17:24:39.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('reccnKhCxCS6w2HfY', 'VitalTac - Script 1046 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', 'Last November a hunter got charged by a grizzly at 40 yards in total darkness. He didn''t fire his rifle. He clicked on his flashlight ‚Äî and the bear turned and ran before it closed half the distance. That flashlight is called VitalTac, and it''s a $600 piece of military hardware that just became available to civilians. Be warned though ‚Äî this is not a toy. It''s basically a handheld weapon that fits in your pack. It''s so powerful that it can illuminate tree lines from hundreds of yards away and even start a fire if your lighter gets wet, making it the ultimate tool for anyone who takes the backcountry seriously. The flashlight projects an incredibly powerful beam of light reaching up to 2 miles, meaning you can spot eyes in the darkness, find your trail, or signal your hunting party from ridgelines away. It was designed specifically for American special forces conducting operations in dense wilderness and hostile terrain at night, where navigation and threat identification in zero visibility was life or death. The flashlight features state-of-the-art military-grade Cree LED technology, making it at least 20 times more powerful than those hunting lights that can barely reach across a field, which gives it the throw distance you actually need when you''re miles from the truck and the sun went down an hour ago. It literally turns night into day wherever you point it. It was designed for special forces and couldn''t be sold to civilians. That is, until a few weeks ago, when an ex-special forces operator who grew up hunting and fishing redesigned the flashlight for outdoor use while retaining all its field-proven functions. He remembered what it was like navigating back to camp with a dying flashlight and knew hunters and outdoorsmen deserved better equipment. He loved these flashlights when he was serving his country, memorized the design and technology so he could build one for serious outdoor use. When he did, he was quickly visited by lawyers telling him that he couldn''t copy the design exactly, or he would get in trouble. He saw this as an opportunity to improve upon it for hunters, campers, and anyone who spends real time in the woods. He adapted it for maximum throw distance, impact resistance for rough terrain, and waterproofing that actually survives creek crossings. It still has all the same functions, strength, and technology as the military version, but now it''s perfectly legal to take into the field. He''s the only one manufacturing it. Having explicit permission to make and sell these in the US, he chose to call his product VitalTac. VitalTac is the most powerful outdoor flashlight ever made, and it''s what serious outdoorsmen have been waiting for. Check out the difference yourself. It even beats a car''s headlights with ease and can light up an entire ridgeline. VitalTac is made from the same purified aluminum and titanium they use on the latest fifth-generation fighter aircraft to withstand enormous pressure and punishment. Meaning that the VitalTac is truly indestructible and will survive every drop, impact, and abuse the backcountry can throw at it. It''s completely waterproof and strong enough to withstand rain, snow, river crossings, and being submerged when you''re fording that creek in the dark. You can even run it over with your truck, and it will keep working because your gear needs to be as tough as the terrain. This flashlight is the perfect outdoor tool for tracking game after dark, navigating back to camp, or spotting predators before they spot you. Its light beam is even powerful enough to start a fire in an emergency, like when your matches are soaked and the temperature is dropping. The VitalTac even has a strobe and SOS function, perfect for signaling your hunting party or calling for rescue if something goes wrong miles from nowhere. If you are interested in the VitalTac, there''s something you should know. While completely legal, this flashlight is not a toy as it''s extremely powerful. The US Product Safety Commission is trying to classify it as military-grade defense equipment. While it will remain perfectly legal to own one, it probably won''t be long before it''s taken off the online market and you''ll be stuck with hunting lights that die when you need them most. That''s also the reason why you can''t buy it from web stores like Amazon or eBay. In fact, if you really want the same capability special forces use in the field, you can only order it from the official website, and today only you can get yours with a 50% discount. Click the link in this video before hunting season and never get caught in the dark again.', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1046, '2026-01-30T17:20:59.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recdXJ2g2U53Wo8HX', 'GhostWing - Script 1029 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('This ninety-nine dollar military drone has Amazon scrambling to remove it from their website. And the reason will shock you.\n\nA former US Army engineer named Captain Adam Scott spent eleven years developing classified drone technology for the Special Forces. His team created something so advanced that enemy positions could be photographed from over a mile away without ever being detected. The Pentagon called it the most significant advancement in aerial reconnaissance in twenty years.\n\nBut here is where the story gets interesting.\n\nAfter retiring from active duty last year, Captain Scott decided to do something that made his former commanders furious. He took the core technology from his military design and rebuilt it for everyday Americans. He stripped out the weapons systems but kept the incredible optical power. He removed the military encryption but preserved the flight stability that makes it virtually crash-proof.\n\nHe calls it GhostWing. And when word got out about what it could do for just ninety-nine dollars, the big drone companies panicked.\n\nHere is why they are terrified. The GhostWing uses something called MOT military optical technology. This is the same system that allows our soldiers to capture crystal-clear images in complete darkness from distances that would be impossible for any consumer drone. We are talking about footage that looks like it came from a ten thousand dollar professional setup.\n\nThe stabilization system alone took four years to develop. It uses the same gyroscope technology found in Apache helicopters. That means you could be shaking like a leaf and your footage still comes out smooth as butter.\n\nBut the feature that