900 meters and brings it home if signal drops or battery gets low.\n\nThe first time I launched it over our backyard, my wife''s jaw dropped. The footage looked like something from a nature documentary. Smooth sweeping shots. Crystal clear detail. Professional quality from two retired teachers who can''t figure out Netflix.\n\nNow she flies it more than I do. She''s captured our grandkids'' soccer games, our golden retriever playing in the lake, our 50th anniversary party. Every video looks like we hired a film crew.\n\nOur neighbor saw the footage and bought one the same day. He''s 78 and had it flying within ten minutes.\n\nThe "Follow Me" feature captures cinematic videos without you touching the controller. It''s completely waterproof, handles freezing cold and scorching heat, and it''s virtually indestructible.\n\nWhen GhostWing launched, it spread like wildfire in the military community. It sold out within 48 hours and developed a waitlist of over 10,000 orders. Professional photographers and filmmakers have made the switch.\n\nAdam has tripled production and is offering a 50%% discount for anyone who orders within the next 24 hours. You can get even deeper discounts by ordering multiple GhostWings, making it a perfect gift.\n\nMy advice: grab one for yourself and a few more for your friends and family before this deal ends. Click on the link below this video to visit the official website and order with 50%% off.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1040, '2026-01-18T08:58:22.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recj4XmblywKJnKZz', 'GhostWing - Script 1062 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('I''ve owned four drones. Crashed every single one ‚Äî expensive ones, cheap ones, didn''t matter, they all ended up in pieces in my backyard. Then my buddy at the VFW handed me this $99 military drone and said "try to break it." I still can''t.\n\nHere''s why. A 44-year-old US Army officer named Captain Adam Scott ‚Äî not a Silicon Valley kid, a real engineer who''s been downrange ‚Äî got assigned to develop something the Special Forces desperately needed for a critical mission in the Middle East. They had to capture enemy positions from miles away without ever being detected. No room for error. No second chances. After months of grinding R&D, Adam and his team built a prototype that command celebrated as the most successful military optical invention in recent years.\n\nThe secret is something called patented MOT military optical technology. It makes this thing at least 20 times more powerful than any drone you''ll find at Best Buy or Amazon. We''re talking crystal-clear 4K footage from tens of miles out. The kind of imagery that used to cost the Pentagon a fortune ‚Äî now packed into a frame that folds smaller than a water bottle and runs 70%% quieter than any standard drone on the market.\n\nAdam looked at what he''d built and knew it was too good to lock inside a classified program. He secured every permission needed, redesigned it for civilian hands, and put it into mass production himself. No corporate middlemen. No $800 markup. Just the guy who invented it selling it directly to people like you and me.\n\nHe called it GhostWing, and it is the most powerful drone ever made available to the public.\n\nAdam developed his own software that increases power and control by 120%%, which means my 74-year-old neighbor flew it on his first try. The "follow me" feature shoots stunning video of you without touching the controller ‚Äî my daughter used it to film my grandkids'' entire Christmas morning from angles I never dreamed possible. Advanced GPS tracks your location within 900 meters and brings it right back to your hand when the signal weakens or the battery gets low. The collision detection means you will not crash this thing ‚Äî I''ve tried. Trust me. Built from military-grade carbon-polymer materials, it''s completely waterproof and handles freezing winters and brutal summer heat without flinching. It flies a 2.7-mile range on a 15-minute flight time, which covers more ground than most people''s entire property.\n\nThis is what changed everything for me. Last spring I had a bad storm rip through. Instead of paying a contractor $300 to climb up and tell me what I already suspected, I sent the GhostWing up and inspected every inch of my roof in four minutes. I survey my whole property line before breakfast now. I keep an eye on my land, my outbuildings, my driveway ‚Äî all from my back porch. The peace of mind alone is worth ten times what I paid.\n\nWhen Adam first launched GhostWing, it spread through the military community like wildfire. Then people started posting their footage online and it exploded. Sold out in 48 hours flat. Over 10,000 orders stacked up on the waitlist. Celebrities and professional filmmakers quietly made the switch. It''s now sitting at over 15,000 five-star reviews from regular folks who can''t believe what they''re getting for this price.\n\nAdam has tripled production and right now he''s offering 50%% off for anyone who orders within the next 24 hours. You can stack even deeper discounts by ordering multiple GhostWings ‚Äî one for you, one for your son, one for your buddy who still thinks drones are too complicated. Every order comes with a 30-day money-back guarantee, so there is zero risk.\n\nClick the link below this video, go to the official site, and grab yours at 50%% off before this deal disappears.\n\nYou''re out on the back porch, coffee''s still warm, and the morning is doing that thing where everything is quiet enough to hear yourself think. You pick up something no bigger than a water bottle, press a single button, and ten seconds later you''re looking down at your entire property from four hundred feet in the air. Every shingle on your roof. Every fence post along your property line. Everything you own, inspected by you, whenever you want, for ninety-nine dollars. Most people have no idea something like this even exists yet.\n\nHere''s the story behind it, and it''s worth hearing. A friend of mine works in defense contracting and last year he wouldn''t stop talking about an Army officer named Captain Adam Scott ‚Äî a forty-four-year-old optical engineer he called the smartest person he''d ever briefed with. Two years ago, the Pentagon assigned Adam and his team a problem most engineers would call impossible. Special Forces needed to photograph enemy positions in the Middle East from miles away without ever being detected. After months of relentless development, Adam''s team built a prototype that stunned every general who reviewed it. Military leadership celebrated it as the most successful optical invention in recent years.\n\nThe secret was something called MOT ‚Äî patented Military Optical Technology. It made Adam''s prototype at least twenty times more powerful than any commercially available drone. That means four-K ultra-wide imagery so sharp you can read a license plate from a distance most cameras can''t even reach. And the entire unit folds down smaller than a water bottle. It operates seventy percent quieter than standard drones, which is exactly why Special Forces trusted it with their lives.\n\nNow here''s where the story turns toward you. Adam looked at what he''d built and realized something. Every homeowner, every grandparent, every person who''s ever paid a contractor three hundred dollars just to climb up and look at a roof ‚Äî they deserved this technology too. As the original creator, he secured every permission needed to redevelop the device for civilian use and ready it for mass production.\n\nHe called it GhostWing, and it is the most powerful personal drone ever engineered.\n\nAdam developed proprietary software that increases the drone''s power and control by one hundred and twenty percent, which means you don''t need experience, you don''t need training, you just press one button. The "follow me" feature lets GhostWing track and film you automatically without touching the controller ‚Äî imagine your grandkids playing in the yard, captured from angles that turn an ordinary afternoon into something your family will watch for years. Advanced GPS locks your location within nine hundred meters and brings GhostWing straight back to you if the signal weakens or the battery gets low. Collision detection prevents any accidental crash, making this the safest quadcopter ever built. The military-grade carbon-polymer frame is completely waterproof and survives freezing winters and scorching summers without a scratch. With a two-point-seven-mile range and fifteen-minute flight time, you cover serious ground every time it goes up.\n\nThink about what this actually means for your life. A storm rolls through tonight ‚Äî tomorrow morning, you survey your own roof in three minutes instead of waiting two weeks for a contractor. You walk your entire property line from your kitchen table. You keep a quiet eye on your home and land anytime you want, day or night. You are independent. You handle your own business. Nobody needs to worry about you, because you''ve got it covered.\n\nWhen Adam first offered GhostWing to the military community, it sold out in forty-eight hours. Then the footage people captured went viral and a waitlist of over ten thousand orders exploded from around the world. Professional photographers and filmmakers made the switch. Over fifteen thousand five-star reviews confirm what Adam already knew ‚Äî nothing else comes close.\n\nAdam has tripled production and is offering a fifty percent discount for the next twenty-four hours ‚Äî backed by a thirty-day money-back guarantee, so there is zero risk. You save even more when you order multiple GhostWings, which makes this the kind of gift people actually remember you for. Click the link below this video right now to visit the official site and claim your fifty percent discount before this offer comes down.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1062, '2026-02-18T16:15:44.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recjYjP9Tifs7fL9f', 'GhostWing - Script 1060 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', 'Everyone told Robert he was too old for a drone. His kids laughed. His neighbor said he''d crash it into a tree. He''s 71, retired, and the most advanced thing he owns is a coffee maker. Then he pressed one button on a $99 military drone and captured footage so stunning his entire family went silent. Now they''re all asking him to buy them one. And the technology behind this device is what makes it all possible. This drone was created specifically for the US Special Forces by Captain Adam Scott, a 44-year-old US Army officer and leading engineer. He and his team were assigned to develop cutting-edge optical equipment for a critical mission in the Middle East. The mission required the Special Forces to capture enemy positions from miles away without ever being detected. After months of research and development, they created a groundbreaking prototype and the results were incredible. Celebrated as the most successful military invention in recent years, it was the first to ever use the patented MOT military optical technology. Meaning it''s at least 20 times more powerful than any commercially available drone, which gives it incredible capabilities. It can literally capture anything from tens of miles away with stunning 4K quality. After seeing the incredible potential of this new technology, Adam quickly realized the impact this device could have on the general public. But he was haunted by something he kept seeing at trade shows and tech expos. Older Americans picking up expensive drones, excited to try something new, only to put them back down after reading the complicated instructions. The look of defeat on their faces stuck with him. He thought if we can make a drone simple enough for a stressed-out soldier in a combat zone, why can''t we make one simple enough for a retiree who just wants to enjoy life? So he decided to make this device available to anyone who wants to try it, with one guiding principle: if it''s not effortless, it''s not ready. As the original creator of the technology, he quickly secured all the permissions needed to redevelop the device and ready it for mass production. He called it Ghostwing and it''s the most powerful drone ever made. It uses a combination of military grade nanotechnology and unique materials to achieve the level of quality and utility of the top drone models but for a fraction of the price. Adam developed his own software that increases the drone''s power and control by 120%, making it so easy to operate that anyone can use it. The secret is what Adam calls "intelligent flight." The Ghostwing thinks for you. It stabilizes itself in wind. It adjusts its own altitude. It frames beautiful shots automatically. All you do is decide when to press the big, clearly-marked button that says "fly." That''s your entire job. The drone handles everything else. It''s loaded with cutting edge technology like the "follow me" feature, which lets you take amazing videos of yourself without even touching the controller. Go for your morning walk. Tend your garden. Play catch with the grandkids. The Ghostwing follows along and films everything like your own personal camera crew. The advanced GPS functionality means it can track your location within 900 meters and return to you quickly when experiencing a weak signal or when the battery is low. It always comes home. And the collision detection function prevents any accidental crash or damage, making this drone the safest quadcopter ever engineered. Fly it near trees, buildings, power lines. It doesn''t matter. It sees obstacles before you do and avoids them automatically. And because it''s made of the best military materials available, it''s virtually indestructible. It''s completely waterproof and strong enough to withstand both freezing and scorching hot temperatures. And what''s best about this drone is that you can use it for thousands of different purposes. Whether you want to finally see your property from above, create stunning travel footage on your next road trip, keep an eye on things when you''re away from home, or simply have a new hobby that gets you outside and excited again, the possibilities with the Ghostwing are endless. It''s also a perfect security tool allowing you to spot anything from a safe distance without ever putting yourself at risk. When Adam first launched Ghostwing, it spread like wildfire in the military community. What he didn''t expect was the wave of messages from people in their 60s and 70s saying the same thing: "This is the first piece of technology that didn''t make me feel stupid." That response overwhelmed him. After going viral, it sold out within the first 48 hours and quickly developed a waitlist of over 10,000 orders from all around the world. Celebrities, professional photographers and filmmakers, all made the switch to it. But it''s the everyday retirees who are calling it their favorite purchase in decades. Adam wants everyone to know about this new technology, so he has since tripled the production and is offering a 50% discount for anyone who orders it within the next 24 hours. You can get even more discounts by ordering multiple Ghostwings, making it a perfect gift for anyone. Especially if you know someone who''s been told they''re too old to learn something new. This is the gift that proves everyone wrong. My advice, grab one for yourself and more for your friends and family before this amazing deal is taken down. Click on the link below this video to visit the official website and order with 50% off.', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1060, '2026-02-10T06:08:08.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recjgGIdAAoDsUvyt', 'GhostWing - Script 1092 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('Your drone footage looks like it was filmed during an earthquake.\n\nEvery single time.\n\nDoesn''t matter if there''s barely any wind. Doesn''t matter if you spent $500 or $800 or $1,000. The moment you try to capture something beautiful, the shaking starts. The wobbling. The footage that makes you look like you handed the controls to a caffeinated squirrel.\n\nThis isn''t your fault.\n\nConsumer drones aren''t built for stability. They''re built to look good on a spec sheet. The companies know their products can''t handle real conditions. They just don''t care.\n\nBut Captain Adam Scott cared.\n\nAdam is a US Army officer who spent years developing drone technology for Special Forces missions in the Middle East. His team needed equipment that could capture enemy positions from miles away in desert sandstorms. In monsoon winds. In conditions that would destroy any civilian hardware.\n\nThey created the first drone ever to use patented MOT military optical technology. Twenty times more powerful than anything commercially available. Stable in winds that would send consumer drones tumbling.\n\nWhen Adam retired, he made this technology available to the public.\n\nHe called it GhostWing.\n\nThe military-grade gyroscopic stabilization holds steady in conditions that make other drones useless. One tester flew his GhostWing in 35 mph gusts. Footage came out smooth as glass.\n\nBut stability isn''t the only thing that sets it apart.\n\nThe GhostWing is silent. Nearly inaudible. The motor technology came from covert operations where noise meant detection. You can fly this at a family event without everyone covering their ears.\n\nIt''s indestructible. Built from the same military composite materials used in tactical aircraft. Waterproof. Temperature resistant. One customer dropped his from 30 feet onto concrete. Picked it up. Kept flying.\n\nAnd anyone can operate it. First try. No experience necessary.\n\nAdam''s software makes the controls so intuitive that complete beginners master it in minutes. One button to launch. One button to land. One button to bring it home automatically. The collision detection prevents crashes before they happen.\n\nThe Follow Me feature turns it into your personal cameraman. Tap your phone and it tracks you automatically. Perfect footage without touching a single control.\n\nWhen GhostWing launched, word spread through the military community instantly. Sold out in 48 hours. Waitlist hit 10,000 orders. Professional photographers and filmmakers made the switch because the quality matches equipment costing twenty times as much.\n\nAdam has tripled production. And right now, he''s offering a 50%% discount for anyone who orders in the next 24 hours.\n\nHalf price. Military-grade technology. Footage that finally looks like what you imagined when you bought your first drone.\n\nOrder multiple and save even more. Perfect for gifts. Perfect for replacing the shaky garbage collecting dust in your closet.\n\nClick the link below to visit the official GhostWing website and claim your discount. Stop settling for earthquake footage. Get the stability the military trusts.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1092, '2026-02-19T17:33:16.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('reck3N1RTDUMHLHAd', 'VitalTac - Script 1018 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('The military didn''t want you to see this.\nThis classified flashlight was NEVER supposed to leave special forces hands. But one soldier broke the rules‚Ä¶ and now you can own one.\nFor years, this $600 tactical light was only issued to elite operators running black ops missions. Why? Because it''s not really a flashlight. It''s a weapon. A beam so intense it can blind enemies from 2 miles away‚Ä¶ and burn through steel like butter.\nHere''s how it got out. A 12-year special forces veteran was sick of watching civilians get robbed, attacked, and left defenseless with garbage flashlights from Amazon. So when he left the service, he memorized the exact military specs‚Ä¶ and built his own. The government sent lawyers to his door within weeks. But here''s the thing ‚Äî he didn''t copy it. He made it BETTER. Changed just enough to make it legal. And now he''s the ONLY person in America allowed to manufacture and sell it.\nHe calls it VitalTac. And nothing else comes close. Watch this ‚Äî it outpowers a car''s high beams like they''re birthday candles. The military-grade Cree LED inside is 20x stronger than any flashlight you''ve ever held. It''s forged from the same aircraft-grade aluminum and titanium they use on F-35 fighter jets. Waterproof. Freezeproof. You can literally run it over with a truck and it keeps working.\nBut here''s what separates VitalTac from everything else: this beam is hot enough to cook food. Start a fire. Signal rescue from miles away with its SOS strobe mode. In a blackout, a disaster, or a home invasion ‚Äî this is the one tool you actually need.\nNow here''s the catch. The US Product Safety Commission is trying to reclassify this as military defense equipment. Once that happens? It''s gone. Pulled from the internet. You won''t find it on Amazon. You can''t get it on eBay. The ONLY place you can buy one is the official site ‚Äî and right now, they''re running a 50%% off flash sale.\nTap the link before the feds shut this down for good.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1018, '2026-01-05T15:43:54.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('reckH370SFiLetmIz', 'GhostWing - Script 1036 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('Amazon keeps trying to remove this $99 military drone from their platform. It''s so powerful that it shoots footage professionals charge $500 an hour to capture‚Äîand the big drone companies want it gone.\n\nIt was created specifically for the US Special Forces by Captain Adam Scott, a 44-year-old US Army officer and lead engineer. He and his team spent 11 years developing classified optical equipment for critical missions in the Middle East. The mission required photographing enemy positions from miles away without ever being detected.\n\nAfter years of intense development, they created a breakthrough prototype. The Pentagon celebrated it as the most significant advancement in aerial reconnaissance in 20 years. It was the first to ever use the patented MOT military optical technology, meaning it''s at least 20 times more powerful than any drone you can buy at Best Buy. This gives it incredible capability.\n\nIt can literally capture anything from miles away with stunning 4K quality.\n\nWhen Adam retired from active duty, he realized the impact this technology could have for regular Americans. So he rebuilt it for civilian use, secured all the permissions needed, and readied it for mass production.\n\nHe called it GhostWing, and it''s the most powerful drone ever made available to the public.\n\nIt uses military-grade nanotechnology and unique composite materials to achieve professional-level quality for a fraction of the price. Adam developed software that increases the drone''s power and control by 120%%, making it so easy that literally anyone can fly it on their first try.\n\nIt''s loaded with technology like the "Follow Me" feature, which captures cinematic videos of you without even touching the controller. The advanced GPS tracks your location within 900 meters and returns the drone to you automatically if the signal drops or the battery gets low.\n\nThe collision detection prevents any crash or damage, making this the safest drone ever engineered. And because it''s made of military-grade materials, it''s virtually indestructible. Completely waterproof. Handles freezing cold and scorching heat.\n\nWhen Adam first launched GhostWing, it spread like wildfire through the military community. A retired Marine posted video of his grandkids playing baseball‚Äîshot entirely on GhostWing‚Äîand it hit 4 million views in three days. People couldn''t believe that quality came from a $99 drone.\n\nThe website crashed from traffic. It sold out within 48 hours and developed a waitlist of over 15,000 orders. Professional photographers and real estate agents have made the switch. Wedding videographers charging $4,000 are losing clients to fathers-in-law with GhostWings.\n\nAdam has tripled production and is offering a 50%% discount for anyone who orders within the next 24 hours. You can get even deeper discounts by ordering multiple GhostWings, making it a perfect gift.\n\nMy advice: grab one for yourself and a few more for your friends and family before this deal disappears. Click on the link below this video to visit the official website and order with 50%% off.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1036, '2026-01-18T08:50:39.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('reckYz1pDHdVnG80M', 'GhostWing - Script 1068 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('A retired schoolteacher from Ohio crashed his brand-new eight-hundred-dollar drone straight into his neighbor''s oak tree on its very first flight. Meanwhile, his fishing buddy next door was quietly capturing stunning aerial footage of the entire neighborhood with a little-known ninety-nine-dollar drone the big companies hope you never hear about.\n\nHere is the strange story behind it. The device was never supposed to reach the public. It was developed under classified conditions by Captain Adam Scott, a forty-four-year-old US Army officer and lead engineer, after his Special Forces unit received an urgent assignment in the Middle East. The mission demanded they photograph enemy positions from miles away without detection, and every existing tool fell short. After months of intensive development, Captain Scott''s team produced a prototype so effective it was celebrated as the most successful optical invention in recent military history.\n\nWhat made it so remarkable was a single breakthrough. The prototype was the first device ever built with patented MOT military optical technology. Independent testing confirmed it performs at least twenty times more powerfully than any commercially available drone. That means crystal-clear four-K imaging from distances that would leave a two-thousand-dollar consumer model completely blind. But the most surprising discovery was still ahead.\n\nCaptain Scott quickly recognized that this technology could solve an expensive problem for millions of ordinary Americans. As the original inventor, he secured every permission needed to adapt the military prototype for civilian use. He redesigned it for simplicity, reduced the manufacturing cost dramatically, and prepared it for mass production. The retail price he settled on stunned even his own team.\n\nHe called it the GhostWing, and at ninety-nine dollars, it is the most powerful drone ever offered to the general public.\n\nHere is exactly what it does. Captain Scott developed proprietary software that increases the drone''s power and responsiveness by one hundred twenty percent, so operating it feels as natural as pointing a television remote. The follow-me feature lets you capture remarkable video of yourself without ever touching the controller. Advanced GPS tracks your position within nine hundred meters and automatically returns the drone when signal weakens or the battery runs low. The collision detection system prevents accidental crashes, making GhostWing the safest quadcopter ever engineered. It is built from military-grade carbon-polymer materials, completely waterproof, and rated to perform in both freezing and extreme heat. It folds smaller than a water bottle, flies seventy percent quieter than standard drones, and covers a two-point-seven-mile range with fifteen minutes of continuous flight.\n\nNow, here is why thousands of Americans over fifty-five are ordering it. You can inspect your roof after a storm without climbing a ladder or paying a contractor three hundred dollars. You can capture footage of your grandchildren playing in the yard that looks like it came from a professional film crew. You can survey your property lines, monitor your home security from a safe distance, and finally see what is actually happening on that back section of your land.\n\nThe results speak for themselves. When Captain Scott first released GhostWing, it sold out completely within forty-eight hours. A waitlist of over ten thousand orders formed almost overnight. The device now holds a four-point-nine-star rating across more than fifteen thousand verified reviews, and every unit ships with a thirty-day money-back guarantee.\n\nBecause production has