ughter''s dance recital, I tapped one button and GhostWing captured the entire performance automatically. Smooth cinematic footage from every angle. Her mother cried watching it. Said it looked more professional than the videographer they''d hired the year before for $800.\n\nNow I''m the family filmmaker. Easter egg hunts. Fourth of July fireworks. My wife''s garden in full bloom. Every video looks like a Hollywood production.\n\nGhostWing is completely waterproof, handles freezing cold and scorching heat, and it''s virtually indestructible. Military-grade materials that survive anything.\n\nOur entire church group bought them after seeing my footage. Six people over 65, all flying within their first week. Pastor Mike is 79 and shoots aerial video of our community events now.\n\nWhen GhostWing launched, it spread like wildfire in the military community. It sold out within 48 hours and developed a waitlist of over 10,000 orders. Professional photographers and filmmakers have made the switch.\n\nAdam has tripled production and is offering a 50%% discount for anyone who orders within the next 24 hours. You can get even deeper discounts by ordering multiple GhostWings, making it a perfect gift.\n\nMy advice: grab one for yourself and a few more for your friends and family. If a 71-year-old who writes checks at the grocery store can do it, so can you. Click on the link below this video to visit the official website and order with 50%% off.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1042, '2026-01-18T08:58:50.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recvIXI8YH28xLqaU', 'VitalTac - Script 1006 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('This flashlight is so dangerous... the government is trying to ban it. And in about 60 seconds you''re gonna see why.\n\nThis military flashlight is basically a real life lightsaber that fits in your pocket.\nBut I gotta warn you right now. This is not some cheap twenty dollar gas station flashlight. At six hundred dollars... this was never meant for civilians. It''s so powerful it melts through solid materials and can start a fire on command.\nThat''s exactly why the military kept it classified. Until now.\nThis thing throws a beam you can see from over two miles away. It was built specifically for American Special Forces. Designed to expose enemy positions in total darkness. And dominate close quarters combat when lives are on the line.\nThe secret is military grade Cree LED technology that makes this at least twenty times more powerful than anything you''ve ever held in your hand. That''s not an exaggeration. That''s why it literally burns through wood... plastic... even metal... in seconds.\nFor years this technology was completely locked away. Civilians couldn''t touch it.\nThen something changed.\nA decorated Special Forces operator retired from service. This man had carried this exact flashlight on missions in places you''ll never hear about. And he couldn''t forget what it meant to him. How many times it kept him alive.\nSo he memorized every detail of the design. And he built one in his garage.\nWithin days... military lawyers showed up at his door. They told him he couldn''t copy the design or he''d face serious consequences.\nMost guys would''ve walked away right there.\nNot him.\nHe saw it as an opportunity. A chance to fix everything that frustrated him during real combat missions. To make it even better. To adapt it for survival... for home defense... for people like you and me.\nAfter months of work he came out with something even more powerful than the original. Same classified technology. Same devastating power. But now completely legal for American civilians to own.\nHe''s the only person in the country licensed to manufacture it.\nHe calls it VitalTac.\nVitalTac is the most powerful flashlight ever sold to the public. And that''s not marketing talk.\nLook at this. See that? It overpowers a car''s headlights without even trying.\nThe body is forged from the same aluminum titanium alloy they use on fifth generation stealth fighter jets. Engineered to survive crushing pressure... extreme heat... and brutal combat conditions.\nWhich means VitalTac is basically indestructible.\nThrow it underwater. Works perfectly.\nFreeze it solid. Fires right up.\nDrop it in boiling water. Not a scratch.\nToss it in open flames. Keeps beaming.\nRun it over with a truck. Still works.\nThere''s nothing you can do to kill this flashlight.\nBut here''s where it gets interesting.\nVitalTac isn''t just tough. It''s a complete survival system.\nThat beam is hot enough to cook food if you need to. Powerful enough to signal rescue helicopters from miles away with the built in SOS mode. And that strobe function? One flash in an attacker''s eyes and they''re blind long enough for you to escape or protect your family.\nThis is the flashlight you hope you never need. But you''ll thank God you had it when everything goes wrong.\nNow if you want one... you need to hear this.\nWhile it''s completely legal right now... the US Product Safety Commission is working to reclassify this as military grade defense equipment. When that happens... it''s gone. You won''t find it anywhere online.\nThat''s already why Amazon won''t touch it. eBay banned it too.\nThe only place you can get a VitalTac is the official website. And right now... today only... you can grab one at fifty percent off.\nClick the link on your screen. See VitalTac in action yourself. And decide if you deserve this kind of protection.\nBefore the government makes that decision for you.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1006, '2025-12-25T18:15:34.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recvXjzxXAxgNV30A', 'GhostWing - Script 1014 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('If you''re over 55 and think drones are "too complicated" for you... you need to see this.\nBecause a retired Army Captain just proved that the drone industry has been lying to you for years.\nThey want you to think flying a drone is hard. They want you to believe it takes weeks of practice. That way, they can keep charging thousands of dollars for "beginner-friendly" models that still leave you confused and frustrated.\nBut here''s the truth they don''t want you to know:\nThe most advanced drone ever created‚Äîoriginally built for US Special Forces‚Äîis actually the easiest drone to fly. And it has nothing to do with your age, your tech skills, or whether you''ve ever touched a controller in your life.\nCaptain Adam Scott is 67 years old. He''s also the lead engineer who developed classified optical technology for a critical mission in the Middle East. His team created the most celebrated military drone in recent history‚Äîthe first ever to use patented MOT military optical technology.\nBut here''s what Adam noticed when he retired:\nHis 71-year-old neighbor wanted to photograph his lakefront property from the air. So he bought a $1,200 "consumer-friendly" drone from a big-name brand. Three weeks later? It was sitting in his garage, untouched. Too many buttons. Too many settings. Too much anxiety about crashing it.\nThat''s when Adam had a realization:\n"If an 82-year-old Army General can fly my military prototype in a sandstorm... why can''t regular Americans fly a drone over their own backyard?"\nThe answer was obvious. Consumer drones aren''t designed for you. They''re designed to look impressive on a spec sheet. Nobody actually thinks about whether a normal person can use them.\nSo Adam did something different.\nHe took the exact technology the Special Forces used‚Äîand he stripped out all the complexity. He kept only what matters: stunning footage, rock-solid stability, and controls so intuitive that his 73-year-old wife flew it perfectly on her very first try.\nHe called it GhostWing.\nAnd it''s completely changing what''s possible for people who thought they''d "missed the boat" on drones.\nHere''s why GhostWing is different:\nIt flies itself. Seriously. Take it out of the box, press one button, and it hovers perfectly in place. No balancing. No calibration. No "learning curve." If you can press an elevator button, you can fly GhostWing.\nIt can''t crash. Military-grade collision detection means it literally refuses to hit obstacles. Trees, walls, your neighbor''s house‚Äîit sees everything and avoids it automatically. One customer told us his grandson tried to crash it into a fence... and the drone just stopped, backed up, and waited for a new command.\nIt comes home on its own. Lose sight of it? Battery getting low? Signal getting weak? GhostWing automatically returns and lands at your feet. You don''t have to do anything.\nIt follows you like a personal cameraman. Want incredible videos of yourself fishing, golfing, or walking the beach with your grandkids? Just tap "Follow Me" and GhostWing does the rest‚Äîno controller needed.\nAnd because it''s built with the same military-grade materials used in the original prototype, this thing is virtually indestructible. Waterproof. Temperature-resistant. Built to last decades, not months.\nNow, here''s what''s happening since word got out:\nRetirees are using GhostWing to photograph their properties, their boats, their RV trips across America. Grandparents are amazing their grandkids with aerial footage of family reunions. One 78-year-old veteran used it to finally photograph the land his father farmed for 50 years.\n‚ÄúUSE VEO3 CUSTOMER TESTEROMIANALS HERE - MAKE THEM OLDER PEOPLE‚Äù\nREVIEW 1: "I haven''t felt this excited about technology since I got my first computer. I was flying it within 5 minutes." \nREVIEW 2: "My son couldn''t believe I was the one flying it. He said it looked like a professional shot it."\nREVIEW 3: "I always assumed drones weren''t for ''people like me.'' I was wrong. This is a blast." \nHere''s the thing: You''re not too old for this.\nYou''ve learned harder things in your life. You''ve adapted to more change than most generations in history. The only reason you don''t have a drone already is because nobody bothered to build one for you.\nUntil now.\nBecause Adam wanted this technology in the hands of as many Americans as possible, he''s cut the price dramatically. While other military-grade drones sell for $2,000+, GhostWing is available today for just $99.\nAnd if you order within the next 24 hours, you''ll lock in an additional 50%% discount‚Äîalong with free priority shipping.\nOrder two or three and you''ll save even more. It makes the perfect gift for a spouse, a sibling, a friend who thinks they''re "too old" for this kind of thing. Prove them wrong.\nBut act fast‚Äîwhen GhostWing launched, it sold out in 48 hours and had a 10,000-person waitlist. Stock is limited and this discount won''t last.\nClick the button below this video to visit the official GhostWing website and claim your discount now.\nIt''s time to stop watching from the sidelines.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1014, '2026-01-05T15:50:28.000Z');
