in the US, he chose to call his product VitalTac. VitalTac is the most powerful flashlight ever made. Check out the difference yourself. It even beats a car''s headlights with ease. VitalTac is made from the same purified aluminum and titanium they use on the latest fifth-generation fighter aircraft to withstand enormous pressure and heat. Meaning that the VitalTac is indestructible.\nIt''s completely waterproof and strong enough to withstand both freezing temperatures, boiling water, as well as flaming hot fire. You can even run it over, and it will keep working. This flashlight is the perfect survival tool. Its light beam is even powerful enough to cook food, like an egg. The VitalTac even has a strobe and SOS function, perfect for emergency situations where visibility is key to survival.\nIf you are interested in the VitalTac, there''s something you should know. While completely legal, this flashlight is not a toy as it''s extremely powerful. The US Product Safety Commission is trying to classify it as military-grade defense equipment. While it will remain perfectly legal to own one, it probably won''t be long before it''s taken off the online market. That''s also the reason why you can''t buy it from web stores like Amazon or eBay. In fact, if you really want one, you can only order it from the official website, and today only you can get yours with a 50%% discount. Click the link in this video for more information about the VitalTac.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1005, '2025-12-25T18:15:32.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recwWsDlAL2aGatNi', 'VitalTac - Script 1039 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('Last Saturday, three houses on my street got broken into in one week. Not across town. Not in some bad neighborhood. My street. And the one thing every cop said when they came to take reports? The houses that got hit were the dark ones.\n\nThere''s something criminals call the soft target scan. Every night, they''re driving through your neighborhood, and they''re not picking houses at random. They''re picking the house that looks the easiest. The one with no lights on out front. The one with a dark walkway. The one where they know they''ll have eight to ten seconds of total darkness between your door and your bedroom to do whatever they want.\n\nSo let me ask you something. If someone was doing that scan on your street tonight, would your house be the one they skip, or the one they circle back to?\n\nBecause here''s what most people don''t realize. It''s not a matter of if your neighborhood gets targeted. It''s a matter of which house. And the only difference between the house that gets passed over and the house that gets broken into is visible deterrence in the first three seconds.\n\nThat''s why when a buddy of mine who spent eleven years in special forces showed me what he carries, I stopped worrying about my street.\n\nHe handed me something at a gun show that looked like an ordinary flashlight. Small, about the size of your hand. But when he clicked it on across the parking lot, I actually stepped back. This thing put out a wall of light so aggressive it felt like staring into a car''s high beams from ten feet away.\n\nHe told me it was built on the same platform they developed for military field operations. Grade five titanium body, the same material they use