saw this, they bought them all. When the internet saw this, the first batch sold out in 48 hours. Over 10,000 people are on the waitlist. But Adam wants to get this into your hands now. So he tripled production. And he is doing something crazy. If you order in the next 24 hours, he is giving you a 50% discount. But you have to hurry. At this price, they are flying off the shelves. Grab one for yourself. Grab a few for Christmas gifts. Don''t be the person who missed out and had to pay full price later. Click the link below. Claim your 50% discount. And see what you‚Äôve been missing.', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1010, '2025-12-18T22:06:53.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recyPMqdwCp73GhTJ', 'VitalTac - Script 1003 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('Lightsabers are finally real‚Äîand starting today, you can carry one. This military-grade flashlight is essentially a pocket lightsaber. But I need to warn you right now: this is NOT a $20 gas station flashlight. At $600, it was never meant for civilians. It''s so devastatingly powerful it melts through solid materials and ignites fire on command‚Äîwhich is exactly why the military kept it classified... until now.\nThis flashlight throws a blinding beam visible from over 2 miles away. It was engineered specifically for American Special Forces‚Äîdesigned to expose enemy positions in total darkness and dominate close-quarters combat when lives hang in the balance.\nThe secret? State-of-the-art military Cree LED technology that makes this thing at least 20 times more powerful than anything you''ve ever held. That''s not marketing hype. That''s why it literally burns through materials in seconds. Wood. Plastic. Even metal. Watch this...\nFor years, this technology was locked away. Civilians couldn''t touch it. Then something changed.\nA decorated Special Forces operator‚Äîa man who''d carried this exact flashlight on countless missions in places you''ll never hear about‚Äîretired from service. But he couldn''t forget what that flashlight meant to him. How it kept him alive. So he memorized every detail of its design... and built one in his garage.\nWithin days, military lawyers showed up at his door. They told him he couldn''t replicate the exact design. Most men would''ve quit right there.\nHe saw it differently.\nHe realized this was his chance to improve on what the military got wrong. To fix the small frustrations that bothered him during real-world missions. To adapt it for survival, for home defense, for you.\nAfter months of refinement, he emerged with something even better than the original. Same devastating power. Same classified technology. But now completely legal for American civilians to own.\nHe''s the only person in the country licensed to manufacture it.\nHe calls it VitalTac.\nVitalTac is, without exaggeration, the most powerful flashlight ever sold to the public.\nDon''t take my word for it‚Äîlook at this comparison. See that? It overpowers a car''s headlights without breaking a sweat.\nThe housing? Forged from the same purified aluminum-titanium alloy used on fifth-generation stealth fighter jets. The same material engineered to survive extreme heat, crushing pressure, and punishing combat conditions.\nTranslation: VitalTac is virtually indestructible.\nSubmerge it underwater? Works perfectly. Freeze it solid? Fires right up. Drop it in boiling water? Not a scratch. Throw it in open flames? Keeps beaming. Run it over with a truck? Still works.\nThere is nothing you can do to kill this flashlight.\nBut VitalTac isn''t just tough‚Äîit''s a complete survival system.\nThat concentrated beam? Hot enough to cook food in an emergency. Powerful enough to signal rescue helicopters from miles away with the built-in SOS mode. And the disorienting strobe function? One flash to an attacker''s eyes and they''re temporarily blinded‚Äîgiving you precious seconds to escape or defend your family.\nThis is the flashlight you pray you never need... but thank God you have when disaster strikes.\nNow‚Äîif you want a VitalTac, there''s something critical you need to understand.\nWhile it''s completely legal to own right now, the US Product Safety Commission is actively working to reclassify this as military-grade defense equipment. Once that happens? You won''t find this online anymore. Period.\nThat''s already why Amazon won''t carry it. Neither will eBay.\nThe only place to secure your VitalTac is the official website. And right now‚Äîtoday only‚Äîyou can claim one at 50%% off the normal price.\nClick the link in this video right now. See the VitalTac in action. And decide for yourself if you deserve this level of protection.\nBefore the government decides for you.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1003, '2025-12-25T18:02:57.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('recya29JWtDfTwO8m', 'VitalTac - Script 1058 - Nick', 'rec3cJmt5H4AENEgZ', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('I''m about to run over this flashlight with my truck.\n\nWatch.\n\nNow watch me turn it on.\n\nStill works. Two thousand pounds of steel and it''s like nothing happened. That''s because this isn''t a flashlight you buy at Home Depot. This is what American special forces actually carry into combat.\n\nIt''s called VitalTac. And until recently, civilians couldn''t own one.\n\nThe story starts with Mike. Twelve years in special operations. He carried a tactical flashlight on every mission that was built to survive explosions, submersion, and extreme temperatures. When he came home, he wanted that same reliability for his family.\n\nBut the military version was classified. $600 per unit. Civilians couldn''t touch it.\n\nSo Mike rebuilt it from scratch. Government lawyers showed up immediately. Said he couldn''t copy the exact design. So Mike improved it. Made it even more durable for civilian applications while keeping all the military capability.\n\nNow he manufactures VitalTac himself. One factory. Total quality control. And the specs are insane.\n\nMilitary-grade Cree LEDs producing 20 times the power of commercial flashlights. A 2-mile beam that turns night into day. Aircraft-grade titanium and aluminum body forged from the same materials as fifth-generation fighter jets.\n\nI''ve put this flashlight through everything.\n\nDropped it from a second-story window. Still works.\n\nSubmerged it in a bucket of water for an hour. Still works.\n\nFroze it in a block of ice overnight. Still works.\n\nRan it over with my truck. You just saw it. Still works.\n\nThis is what happens when military engineering meets civilian need. Equipment designed by people who couldn''t afford failures. Equipment tested in the worst conditions on earth.\n\nWatch what happens when I compare it to car headlights. VitalTac makes them look dim. That concentrated beam can literally start fires. Point it at dry kindling, wait ten seconds, and you''ve got flames. No matches. No lighter. Just light.\n\nThere''s a strobe mode that special forces use to disorient threats. Flash it in someone''s eyes and they can''t see for minutes. Completely non-lethal but incredibly effective. There''s also an SOS function for signaling rescue.\n\nHere''s the situation.\n\nThe Product Safety Commission is trying to classify this as military-grade defense equipment. It''s still completely legal to own right now. But once that classification goes through, online sales stop. It''s already banned from Amazon and eBay.\n\nThe only way to get VitalTac is through Mike''s official website.\n\nHe could charge $300 and sell out instantly. The military pays $600. But Mike built this for American families. He wants it accessible to people who need real equipment.\n\nSo right now, today only, VitalTac is available at 50%% off.\n\nI''ve bought dozens of flashlights over the years. Every brand you can name. None of them could survive what VitalTac just did. None of them could perform like VitalTac does.\n\nThis is equipment you buy once and trust forever.\n\nClick the link below this video. See all the demonstrations on the official page. Watch the fire-starting test. Watch the underwater test. Watch the freeze test.\n\nThen grab yours before the discount disappears.\n\nReal equipment for real situations.\n\nClick now.'), 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1058, '2026-02-19T17:50:24.000Z');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO video_scripts (id, script_name, product_id, author_id, script_content, is_approved, needs_revision, version, notes, hook, body, hook_number, base_script_number, created_at) VALUES ('reczediTJRdKvZW9f', 'GhostWing - Script 1085 - Nick', 'recMS4kpPubp6bHyu', 'recaidhXBfNk3aUQI', printf('A retired Navy SEAL just went public with something drone companies have been hiding for years.\n\nThey don''t want you to know this exists.\n\nSee, Commander Jake Reynolds spent 24 years in special operations. Flew classified surveillance missions in places he still can''t talk about. When he retired last spring, he thought buying a consumer drone would be simple.\n\nHe was wrong.\n\nFirst drone he bought cost $800. Supposed to be top of the line. Took it out to film his ranch in Montana. Wind picked up to maybe 15 miles an hour. The footage looked like it was shot during an earthquake. Shaky. Unusable. Garbage.\n\nHe returned it. Bought another brand. $600 this time. Flew it once. Clipped a fence post. Shattered into pieces.\n\nJake was furious. Not because of the money. Because he knew better technology existed.\n\nHe''d used it himself. In combat.\n\nThat''s when he made some calls to old military contacts. And discovered something that made his blood boil.\n\nThe technology for rock-solid, whisper-quiet drone flight has existed for over a decade. The military has it. Hollywood has it. But consumer drone companies deliberately hold it back. They sell you garbage that breaks, then sell you more garbage.\n\nUntil one man decided to change everything.\n\nCaptain Adam Scott, a 44-year-old Army officer and lead engineer, developed classified optical equipment for Special Forces missions in the Middle East. His team created the first drone ever to use patented MOT military optical technology. It''s at least 20 times more powerful than anything commercially available.\n\nWhen Adam retired, he did something unprecedented. He secured permission to bring this technology